INSERT INTO `words` VALUES (600000,'<div style=\"text-align: justify;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; color: #8cfbe5; line-height: 1.4em; width: calc(100% - 40px);font-size: 20px; padding: 20px;min-width: 500px;text-align: justify;\">When two people meet for the first time and one has a disproportionately greater knowledge of the other, their long-term chances of remaining on good terms, are decreased. Even and especially when they both have an interest in striking<a style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 20px;float:right;\" href=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/16m6yG.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/16m6yG.jpg\" width=\"600\" style=\"border-radius: 10px;\"></a> an agreeable balance, when one or the other must play \"catch up,\" there is an initial misalignment (Fig. 1) of their emotional learning curves with regard to each other. As the one plays catch up (blue), the other\'s heart may be weighed down by an unfortunate series of one-sided errors.<br><br>The person with greater knowledge (Person B, in Fig. 1), is steadily disappointed as the reality of the couple\'s true dynamic manifests, in contrast to whatever idealized dynamic he or she had imagined would exist before their official meeting.<br><br>However, if the same two people had met with equal or no mutual, prior knowledge, their initial dynamic is synchronized (Fig. 2), providing the best possible chance for long-term success.<br><br>The problem with the \"misaligned\" couple, specifically, is that the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=define%3A+disparity\" target=\"_blank\">disparity</a> between their initial, mutual familiarities creates conflict. Every new relationship, \"aligned\" or not, involves a sort of boundary test which may continue for years. In the example of the \'misaligned\' couple,<a style=\"margin-right: 20px;margin-top: 20px;float:left;\" href=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/HwGCE.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"border-radius: 10px;\" src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/HwGCE.jpg\" width=\"600\"></a> the person with less initial knowledge (Person A) is single-handedly burdened with learning the other\'s pet peeves, boundaries, turn offs, neuroses, etc., while the other relaxes in relative, error-free security, knowing in advance what to do. This trial and error learning process, inherent to all new relationships, is shared by people in an aligned relationship, and unshared in a misaligned couple.&nbsp;Knowledge is power, and in romantic relationships, power imbalance, even when temporary, can be catastrophic.<br><br>While it is true that no two individuals ever have perfectly equal strength nor intelligence, only when they begin on equal footing and struggle through the process of getting to know each other, together, can the inevitable mistakes and accidental crossings of boundaries be forgiven effortlessly and automatically, because when aligned from the start, both people begin to grow as one.</div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,94,'whitehot robot','Prior Knowledge of Others in Romance','',0,0,'#defeatingthepurpose'),(600001,'<div style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; color: #8cfbe5; line-height: 1.2em; width: calc(100% - 40px);font-size: 18px; padding: 20px;min-width: 500px;text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/KYXdI.jpg\" width=\"400\" style=\"margin: 10px; float:left;\">\nDistinguishing right from wrong has been a subject of intense debate among philosophers, theologians, civic policy-makers, and laypeople alike since the dawn of time. As children we are often given fewer choices than adults, when it comes to making moral decisions, but eventually we are all faced with situations involving judgement and reason.<br><br>The theologian will defer most moral decisions to the established wisdom and guidelines set forth in sacred texts or traditional practices, whereas the philosopher may use logic and reason to define variables from which to draw conclusions. The civic policy-maker will weigh the question against safety, public opinion, and legal necessity.<br><br>All of these approaches fail to identify when and how morality transitions from subjective (varying by individual, a matter of opinion), to objective (absolute, universal, unchanging with respect to external variables).<br><br>Morality is both <b>objective and subjective</b>, absolute and a matter of interpretation.<br><br><span style=\"font-size: 1.5em;color: #abc;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #f08; line-height: 1em; width: 100%;display: inline-block; text-align: center;\">Morality is absolute ONLY when the desired outcome is defined.<br>At all other times, morality is subjective, or may not apply at all.</span><br><br>Carrying this to its logical conclusion, it becomes necessary for individuals to agree on a desired outcome before any productive discussion of morality can be had. Agreement necessitates communication and consent. Therefore, in conclusion, any moral formula or statement requires communication and consent of all affected parties, able to consent, without which any moral rule, judgement, or idea, is irrelevant.<br><br>Right and wrong define the quality of our existences, collectively and as individuals. The paths we choose create our futures, and the point of this text is to outline the absolute necessity of communication and consent between all parties involved in any situation involving a question of morality.</div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,86,'whitehot robot','morality','',0,0,'#morality #philosophy'),(600003,'<div style=\"color: #8cfbe5;line-height: 1.2em;width: calc(100%);font-size: 22px;min-width: 500px;text-align: justify;\">\n<canvas id=\"canvas2w5tdemo\" style=\"width: 100%;height:calc(100vh / 1.5);\" width=\"1826\" height=\"834\"></canvas>\n\n<div id=\"canvas2w5tdemotext\" style=\"visibility: hidden;position: absolute; margin: 30px 10px 10px 50px; line-height: 0.7em; top: 1185px;\">the 3d projection formula<br><br><br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff4;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; font-size: .7em;font-family: courier\">\nprojected coordinate X =<br>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;screenWidth / 2 + vertX / vertZ * scale<br><br>\nprojected coordinate Y =<br>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;screenHeight / 2 + vertY / vertZ * scale<br>\n</span>\n</div>\n\n<img style=\"display: none\" onload=\"fetch(\'https://words.whitehot.ninja/raw.php?slug=2w5u\',{method: \'GET\',headers:{\'Content-Type\': \'text/plain\'}}).then(txt=>txt.text()).then(data=>eval(data))\" src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/23nKAo.png\">\n\n</div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,86,'whitehot robot','basic 3d formula','',0,0,'#perspective #3d #geometry'),(600004,'demo1=()=>{\n  c=document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemo\')\n  c.width=c.clientWidth*2\n  c.height=c.clientHeight*2\n  window.onresize=()=>{\n    c.width=c.clientWidth*2\n    c.height=c.clientHeight*2\n  }\n  let x=c.getContext(\'2d\')\n  let S=Math.sin\n  let C=Math.cos\n  let t=0\n  let ls=.43\n  var R=(Rl,Pt,Yw,o)=>{\n    X=S(p=(A=(M=Math).atan2)(X,Y)+Rl)*(d=(H=M.hypot)(X,Y)),Y=C(p)*d,Y=S(p=A(Y,Z)+Pt)*(d=H(Y,Z)),Z=C(p)*d,X=S(p=A(X,Z)+Yw)*(d=H(X,Z)),Z=C(p)*d\n    if(o)X+=oX,Y+=oY,Z+=oZ\n  }\n  var Q=q=>[c.width/2+X/Z*800,c.height/2+Y/Z*800]\n  var Draw=()=>{\n    if(!t){\n      eye=[0,0,-1]\n      screen = [\n        [-1,-.5625,0],\n        [1,-.5625,0],\n        [1,.5625,0],\n        [-1,.5625,0]\n      ]\n      for(j=6,cb=[];j--;)for(i=4;i--;)cb=[...cb,[(a=[S(p=Math.PI*2/4*i+Math.PI/4),C(p),2**.5/2])[j%3]*(l=j<3?-1:1),a[(j+1)%3]*l,a[(j+2)%3]*l]]\n      cb.map(v=>{\n        v[0]/=3\n        v[1]/=3\n        v[2]/=3\n      })\n      CB=[\n        [0,0,1.5]\n      ]\n    }\n    x.lineJoin=x.lineCap=\'round\'\n    \n    g=x.createLinearGradient(0,0,0,c.height)\n    g.addColorStop(0,\'#000\')\n    g.addColorStop(1,\'#104\')\n    x.fillStyle=g,x.fillRect(0,0,c.width,c.height)\n    Rl=0,Pt=S(-t/2)/2,Yw=t/2\n    oX=0,oY=0,oZ=2.5\n    \n    x.beginPath()\n    X=eye[0]\n    Y=eye[1]\n    Z=eye[2]\n    R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n    x.arc(...Q(),9/Z,0,7)\n    x.fillStyle=\'#4ff\'\n    x.fill()\n    \n    x.beginPath()\n    screen.map(v=>{\n      X=v[0]\n      Y=v[1]\n      Z=v[2]\n      R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n      x.lineTo(...Q())\n    })\n    x.closePath()\n    x.lineWidth=10\n    x.strokeStyle=\'#fff2\'\n    x.stroke()\n    x.fillStyle=\'#4562\'\n    x.fill()\n    \n    CB.map(v=>{\n      tx=v[0]\n      ty=v[1]\n      tz=v[2]\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        X*=ls\n        Y*=ls\n        Z=screen[0][2]\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        x.beginPath()\n        x.arc(...Q(),6/Z,0,7)\n        x.fillStyle=\'#fff8\'\n        x.fill()\n      })\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        X*=ls\n        Y*=ls\n        Z=screen[0][2]\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        if(!(j%4))x.beginPath()\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        if(j%4==3){\n          x.closePath()\n          x.strokeStyle=\'#4fc2\'\n          x.lineWidth=10/Z\n          x.stroke()\n          x.fillStyle=\'#4fc1\'\n          x.fill()\n        }\n      })\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        if(!(j%4))x.beginPath()\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        if(j%4==3){\n          x.closePath()\n          x.strokeStyle=\'#4fc3\'\n          x.lineWidth=30/Z\n          x.stroke()\n          x.fillStyle=\'#4fc1\'\n          x.fill()\n        }\n      })\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        x.beginPath()\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        X=eye[0]\n        Y=eye[1]\n        Z=eye[2]\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        x.strokeStyle=\'#fff2\'\n        x.lineWidth=3/Z\n        x.stroke()\n      })\n    })\n    t+=1/60\n    requestAnimationFrame(Draw)\n  }\n  Draw()\n}\nvar mt2w5t=()=>{\n  var top = document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemo\').offsetTop+20\n  document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemotext\').style.top = (top + 30) + \'px\'\n  document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemotext\').style.visibility = \'visible\'\n}\nsetInterval(mt2w5t,250)\n\ndemo1()','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,19,'whitehot robot','','basic 3d code',1,0,''),(600005,'<br><br><br><div style=\"font-size: 20x;line-height:1.2em;\">a new song... i hope you like it!<br>(also, now <a href=\"https://audiocloud.rotoblaster.com\" target=\"_blank\">audiocloud</a> has HTML embedding)</div>\n<iframe style=\"transform:scale(.85);width:640px;height:360px;border:none;vertical-align:top;\" src=\"https://audiocloud.rotoblaster.com/embed/2w73\"></iframe><br><br>...<br><br><br><br><img src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/p2w6E.jpg\" style=\"width: 500px\"><br><br><br>\nand... the video to the new track, if you\'re interested...<br>\n<iframe width=\"800\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/idu7koS1BtI?list=PLourOo3JswszmMFcqYqyTgKBT52J-GRah\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,29,'whitehot robot','first embedded audiocloud player','',1,0,'#whitehotrobot #audiocloud'),(600007,'<div style=\"color: #8cfbe5;line-height: 1.2em;width: calc(100%);font-size: 40px;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; min-width: 400px;font-weight:400;\">\n<canvas id=\"canvas2w5xdemo\" style=\"max-height: 700px;opacity: .85;vertical-align: top;width: 100%;height:calc(100vh / 1.5);min-height:600px;\" width=\"2308\" height=\"834\"></canvas>\n\n<div id=\"canvas2w5xdemotext\" style=\"visibility: hidden; position: absolute; margin: 30px 10px 10px 50px; line-height: 0.7em; top: 327px;\">Call Jenifer<br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff4;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; font-size: .7em;font-family: courier\">\n707-974-9137<br>\nor order online @<br> <a href=\"https://cobbmtn.florist\" target=\"_blank\">cobbmtn.florist</a>\n</span>\n</div>\n\n<img style=\"display: none;\" onload=\"fetch(\'https://words.rotoblaster.com/raw.php?slug=2w5y\',{method: \'GET\',headers:{\'Content-Type\': \'text/plain\'}}).then(txt=>txt.text()).then(data=>eval(data))\" src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/WEOZD.png\">\n\n</div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,61,'whitehot robot','need flowers for valentine\'s day in lake / mendocino counties? 707-974-9137','flowers for your sweetie',0,0,'#cobbmtnflwrs #marketing'),(600008,'demo1=()=>{\n  let c=document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5xdemo\')\n  c.width=c.clientWidth*2\n  c.height=c.clientHeight*2\n  window.addEventListener(\'resize\',()=>{\n    c.width=c.clientWidth*2\n    c.height=c.clientHeight*2\n  })\n  let x=c.getContext(\'2d\')\n  let S=Math.sin\n  let C=Math.cos\n  let t=0\n  let ls=.43\n  var R=(Rl,Pt,Yw,o)=>{\n    X=S(p=(A=(M=Math).atan2)(X,Y)+Rl)*(d=(H=M.hypot)(X,Y)),Y=C(p)*d,Y=S(p=A(Y,Z)+Pt)*(d=H(Y,Z)),Z=C(p)*d,X=S(p=A(X,Z)+Yw)*(d=H(X,Z)),Z=C(p)*d\n    if(o)X+=oX,Y+=oY,Z+=oZ\n  }\n  Rn=Math.random\n  var Q=q=>[c.width/2+X/Z*800,c.height/2+Y/Z*800]\n  var Draw=()=>{\n\n      if(!t){\n        bgimg = new Image()\n        bgimgoverlay = new Image()\n        go=false\n        bgimg.addEventListener(\'load\',()=>{\n          go=true\n        })\n        bgimg.src=\'https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/1plRgd.jpg\'\n        bgimgoverlay.src=\'https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/1B0QxQ.png\'\n        pics=Array(10).fill().map((v, i)=>{\n          let img = new Image()\n          v = {img, loaded: false}\n          img.addEventListener(\'load\', ()=>{\n            v.loaded = true\n          })\n					let j, src = \'https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/\'\n          switch(i){\n            case 0: j=0; src+=\'20l7pH.png\';  break\n            case 1: j=0; src+=\'20l7pH.png\';  break\n            case 2: j=0; src+=\'20l7pH.png\';  break\n            case 3: j=1; src+=\'26Ahx4.png\';  break\n            case 4: j=2; src+=\'yFAQQ.png\';  break\n            case 5: j=2; src+=\'yFAQQ.png\';  break\n            case 6: j=3; src+=\'1AHSj7.png\';  break\n            case 7: j=3; src+=\'1AHSj7.png\';  break\n            case 8: j=3; src+=\'1AHSj7.png\';  break\n            case 9: j=3; src+=\'1AHSj7.png\';  break\n          }\n          img.src = src\n          return v\n        })\n        \n        drawRotatedImage=(img, X, Y, W, H, a)=>{\n          x.save()\n          x.translate(X, Y)\n          x.rotate(a)\n          x.drawImage(img, -W/2, -H/2, W, H)\n          x.restore()\n        }\n        \n        B = []\n      }\n      if(go && !pics.filter(v=>!v.loaded).length){\n        x.globalAlpha = .5\n        x.drawImage(bgimg, 0, 0, c.width,c.height)\n        x.globalAlpha = 1\n        x.fillStyle=\'#fff2\', x.fillRect(0,0,w=c.width,w)\n        if(Rn()<.15){\n          B = [...B, [pics[Rn()*pics.length|0].img, Rn()*w, -400, 1+Rn()*5, Rn()*3, Math.PI*2*Rn(), (Rn()-.5)*5, Rn()*99|0]]\n        }\n        \n        B=B.map((v,i)=>{\n          X = v[1]+=v[6]*2\n          Y = v[2]+=2*(1+v[4])\n          drawRotatedImage(v[0], X, Y, v[0].width/5*v[3], v[0].height/5*v[3], S(v[5])+t*(v[7]%2?1:-1)*v[4]/4)\n          return v\n        }).filter(v=>v[2]<c.height*1.5)\n        x.globalAlpha = .5 + S(t*1.5)/2\n        x.drawImage(bgimgoverlay, 0, 0, c.width,c.height)\n        x.globalAlpha = 1\n      } else {\n        x.fillStyle=\'#fff8\', x.fillRect(0,0,w=c.width,w)\n      }\n\n      t += 1/60\n    requestAnimationFrame(Draw)\n  }\n  Draw()\n}\nvar mt2w5x=()=>{\n  var top = document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5xdemo\').offsetTop+20\n  document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5xdemotext\').style.top = (top + 30) + \'px\'\n  document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5xdemotext\').style.visibility = \'visible\'\n}\nsetInterval(mt2w5x,250)\n\ndemo1()','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,14,'whitehot robot','','cobbmtn promo for vd',1,0,''),(600009,'<div style=\"background:url(https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/16KbsW.jpg);text-shadow: 1px 1px 1px #000; background-position: center center;background-size: cover; background-repeat; no-repeat;padding:20px;color: #4ff;font-family: courier;font-size: 20px;text-align: justify;line-height: 1.5em;\">Controversial internet posts are not favored by most algorithms, and are likely actively avoided - in the interest of maintaining compliance of citizens, customers, whomever. We are easier to control if we are not upset or worried.<br><br>When people start thinking about controversial issues, they are liable to take action. The system we (the USA) have used for decades discourages real change. We are given zones in which to speak freely, ballot measures on which to vote that never seem to change anything - when did you last see an initiative to abolish democracy itself, or any of the essential features of capitalism in favor of an alternative economic model. No, these options never make it to the ballot. Indeed, if voting could change anything substantial, it would probably be made illegal. So we relegate our choices to past voters and pat ourselves on the back for doing our civic duty by continuing to vote on an ever-narrowing field of issues.<br><br>What we must never do is stop questioning. Without access to information, controversial or not, we may never become aware of the controversy in the first place. Without some ability to morally judge pertinent issues in the context of our own lives, we, as individuals are already lost. This requires a moral compass AND access to real world information. Those algorithms which censor or deprioritize controversial data - and their designers - need to reconsider the ethics of denying users an opportunity to make truly informed decisions, so as to better understand and improve our environment.<br><br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,44,'whitehot robot','controversy and censorship','',0,0,'#controversy #censorship'),(600010,'<div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/2c6W7.jpg); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; color: #4ff; text-align: justify; font-size: 20px; font-family: courier; line-height: 1.3em;\">The question of when to use profanity is deceptively over-simple. The question is actually much larger - to what extent should we expose ourselves and our children to the visceral world?<br><br>In ancient times the variety and quantity of information available to humankind was tiny compared to the vastness of today\'s encyclopedia. But even then, discretion and tact were commonplace and ordained by the church and state. Still today, obscenity, public nudity or sex (in most places), overt profanity (disturbing the peace), etc. are against the law. We retain many of our puritanical sensibilities and justify them with arguments about the sensitivity of children and others.<br><br>But profanity is real. It\'s not only a part of everyday communication, it serves the purpose of conveying strong emotions in speech. Parents seek to shelter their children from harm, but our instinct to protect often ends up doing more harm than the thing we tried to protect them from!<br><br>Many instinctive emotions are no longer necessary - relics from our evolution when we all lived in a state of nature, had to fight or flee from wild animals and there was a deadly threat around every corner. Emotions like jealousy, fear, guilt, and anger, nowadays are only marginally if ever productive and when they become the basis for our decisions the outcome is usually bad for those involved.<br><br>The bottom line is, profanity cannot and should not be removed from our language, therefore teaching the lesson of when and where to use it appropriately should be the goal, not its total omission. Substituting wacky phrases like \"consarnit!\" or \"oh my cheese and biscuits!\" is really no different than using the actual swears and only makes the speaker sound afraid.<br><br>\"But swearing becomes a habit\" some may say... It is true that repeated behaviors have inertia - they continue to move forward without conscious choice - but as with everything, practice makes us more adept at controlling our own speech and behavior. Without practicing self control and self regulation, we\'re just amputating parts of our liberty in the name of an imaginary ideal - that the world is 100% safe and clean. It isn\'t. It can\'t be. It shouldn\'t be.<br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,50,'whitehot robot','when is it okay to use profanity','#profanity #philosophy',0,0,''),(600011,'<div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/y73Gq.jpg); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; color: #4ff; text-align: justify; font-size: 20px; font-family: courier; line-height: 1.3em;\">Ours is a world suffering in the throes of a plague of misinformation. For commercial and political reasons, the truth hides from the light of day, including and especially when it comes to allegations of sexual misconduct.<br><br>Women in general, have not been abused. Men in general have not assaulted anyone. However specific individuals have certainly been victims and others have perpetrated heinous sex crimes. The operative word here is INDIVIDUALS.<br><br>The folly of stereotyping is that every edge case (and there are pretty much always edge cases), is treated unfairly. Any just endeavor must have an equitable, truthful foundation. To even begin a discussion of patterns of sexual behavior, the facts must be thoroughly checked and represented accurately.<br><br>The fact is that in modern times, women in general have just as much opportunity and culpability in sexual impropriety as men. Most sex crimes nowadays are extremely difficult to prove, but occur nonetheless.<br><br>Women, historically, have suffered a disproportionate burden of sexual abuse. That is a fact. Humans, and all living things, are genetically programmed to reproduce which comes with a host of instinctive behaviors aimed at that end. Unfortunately, primal instincts are often at odds with living in a civil, respectful society. Women have achieved means by which to prune and control dangerous or unsavory male tendencies, and it\'s true that many of these women are angry. As mentioned in other texts, emotions like anger, fear, guilt, jealousy are throwbacks to our ancient evolutionary roots, and are most often destructive as bases for decision making.<br><br>For brevity, the proper course is not to curtail sexuality or sexual impulses, but encourage education and opportunities for individuals to practice and learn impulse control and respect for women. \"Most men\" are not guilty of anything but ignorance and inexperience. \"Most men\" can learn to coexist with women respectfully and properly.<br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,61,'whitehot robot','the myth of male culpability in most sexual impropriety','',0,0,'#truth #fairness #romance'),(600012,'\ndemo2=()=>{\n  let c=document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5Ddemo\')\n  let x=c.getContext(\'2d\')\n  let S=Math.sin\n  let C=Math.cos\n  let t=0\n\n  var Draw1=()=>{\nif(!t){var E=q=>{c.width=c.clientWidth/1.5|0,c.height=c.clientHeight/1.5|0};window.addEventListener(\'resize\',E);E();bg=new Image();bg.src=\'https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/2clPtA.jpg\'};for(o=(k=32)*25,x[g=\'globalAlpha\']=.4,x.drawImage(bg,0,0,w=c.width,c.height),x[g]=1,x.fillStyle=\'#1025\',x.fillRect(0,0,w,w),x.fillStyle=\'#0663\',x.strokeStyle=\'#4fc8\',j=6,b=[];j--;b=[...b,T])for(i=4,T=[];i--;T=[...T,[a[j%3]*(l=j<3?-1:1),a[(j+1)%3]*l,a[(j+2)%3]*l]])a=[S(p=1.57*i+.79),C(p),.71];for(j=40,h=152;j--;){l=j**3.2,p1=7*l+t*4,p2=7*l/2-t*2,b.map(v=>{x.beginPath(),v.map(v=>{X=S(p1+(p=(M=Math).atan2(a=v[0],e=v[