iness ever exist?<br><br>Happiness CAN exist, and its recipe is surprisingly simple. Only 2 parts, really.<br><br><center><b>1) Eliminate undue suffering by desiring only what you have<br>2) Expend time, emotions, and energy only on people and things within your sphere of control</b></center><br>These guidelines are easier said than done. When we are forced to constantly be aware of and compare our lives and situations to others, when we are told by every commercial, billboard, radio jingle, etc. that we are sick and suffering and that we need some product to cure us, when we become involved in situations over which we have no realistic influence, when we feel (usually erroneously) that our needs have gone unmet in romance or finance - happiness becomes an ever more distant and fictional-seeming ideal.<br><br>Life is absurd. Life comes with no guarantees. What\'s important to one person need not be important to another. Our happiness is subverted daily by those who suffer from the desire to possess that which they do not have but desperately WANT - more money, more freedom, more love, more purpose.<br><br>Happiness is additive. That is, one person\'s happiness does not infringe on the happiness of others. Just as the success of a group\'s member only strengthens the group, rather than, as most of us are wrongly taught, must come at the cost of someone else\'s happiness or success.<br><br>The real danger and tragedy is, if enough people become unhappy enough, bad things start to happen for all of us. Citing examples would only invite attempts at disproof, but you can imagine what a nation or world of unhappy people may do to themselves and others.<br><br>Take stock. Acknowledge this moment. Be self focused and present and know that everything in your sphere is a gift - a rare and beautiful opportunity to experience something, as improbable as experience is, you exist to be happy, at least sometimes.<br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,62,'whitehot robot','happiness','',0,0,'#happiness #philosophy #psychology'),(600017,'<div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/WYku4.jpg); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; color: #8ff; text-align: center; font-size: 20px; font-family: courier; line-height: 1.5em;\">\n<span style=\"font-size: 32px;font-weight: 900;\"><br>UPDATE<br></span><br>words.rotoblaster.com now has version control for all posts!<br>backups happen at regular intervals, so now users can harness them.<br>while many backups may exist on the server,<br>only unique versions are displayed.&nbsp;<br><br><img src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/nTTKw.png\"><br><br><br><br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,54,'whitehot robot','version control!','',0,1,'#updates'),(600018,'<div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/WYku4.jpg); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; color: #8ff; text-align: center; font-size: 20px; font-family: courier; line-height: 1.5em;\">\n<span style=\"font-size: 32px;font-weight: 900;\"><br>MAJOR UPDATE<br></span><br><a href=\"https://code.rotoblaster.com\">code.rotoblaster.com</a> now has version control, like words.rotoblaster.com, for all posts!<br>Also there is now a search function, pagination, styling and performance upgrades, a new \"private\" button which controls demos visibility (on the home page). The comments section has some improved functionality and styling as well. Lastly, a footer menu has been added to house the buttons/links to the other whitehot robot tools, to make room for the nav buttons in the header &lt;3 &nbsp;<br><br><a href=\"https://code.rotoblaster.com/d/2w5s\"><img src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/UWbL4.png\"></a><br><br><br><br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,64,'whitehot robot','major overhaul of demo/code platform for musicians','',0,0,'#update'),(600019,'<div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/fyUo2.jpg); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; color: #8ff; text-align: justify; font-size: 20px; font-family: courier; line-height: 1.5em;\">\nIn the last few hundred years economic theorists of the world have resided in basically one of two camps - communism/socialism, or capitalism. One or the other of these models have been favored by nations, each for their own reasons.<br><br>On one hand capitalism has been touted by western nations as essential for promoting product innovation and price control. When businesses are forced to compete under capitalism, the consumer is free to decide between companies and products. A company with lower prices or higher quality products will be favored in the marketplace and emerge dominant, until its competitors rise to the challenge, providing yet better quality products at even lower prices. And so on it goes.&nbsp; Sounds good? Unfortunately there are natural limits to how advanced products can become and how productive people can and should be...<br><br>Another big catch in capitalism is when there is no significant competition, a monopoly exists, which may result in price gouging, profiteering, and a pattern of declining product quality. Moreover, traditional capitalism involves allowing popularity to justify product existence, usually creating an unfair, unhealthy atmosphere within communities.<br><br>Under communism, on the other hand, the production of goods and services&nbsp; and their prices are strictly regulated by the government. The issue of monopolies is avoided, but the drawback is that there is less or no incentive to innovate or progress forward as an economy.<br><br>Modern economies in capitalistic nations are no longer strictly capitalistic, but still operate under the guidelines of capitalism. This creates huge problems like, when technology has made it extremely easy for competing companies to align their prices, they do, thereby creating a monopoly situation with all its pitfalls, but as separate companies they avoid charges of being monopolies. The result, as mentioned is a steady decline in product quality and increase in prices, sound familiar?<br><br>The solution is to impose authoritative oversight on the marketplace, disallowing toxic pricing, practices, and products, while still allowing competition between businesses which are not natural monopolies, and regulating those businesses which are natural monopolies.<br><br>It\'s a big subject, but problems do have solutions.<br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,80,'whitehot robot','the free market and its utility','',0,0,''),(600021,'<div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/27vYZM.jpg); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; color: #8ff; text-align: justify; font-size: 20px; font-family: courier; line-height: 1.5em;\">\n<center><br>\"One man calling another man crazy... psh!\" he said.</center><br>To start, there are, as the experts put it, organic or hereditary pathological, neurological conditions which exist. To define them would require a book with as many pages as there are people - which is what we have: the DSM-5 (Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, 5th Edition), which tries to accurately describe every conceivable form of psychiatric ailment.<br><br>There is not a human alive who has not exhibited some behavior in this book. Moreover, the book and others like it, has become more of a weapon against the people than an instrument of healing. Its definitions can and do apply to anyone, which makes it a convenient catch-all to justify legal action against people accused of crimes but who are not good candidates for incarceration.<br><br>More generally, contemporary understanding of \"mental illness\" has become a witch hunt. We\'re ever on the lookout for the next crazy person, and many of us question our own mental health when the real culprit is a woefully unnatural, restrictive environment.<br><br>We are born into this world trusting and that trust leads us to believe that others are wiser and would not allow harm to come to us - that if something BIG were wrong with the world, they would fix it. But our trust in this case is misplaced. As history has proven countless times, humanity\'s natural course does not always go in a healthy direction. Sometimes radical reform is the only solution. Sometimes, for example during the renaissance, the whole world wakes up as if from a dream to a new reality, shattering past illusions and revealing what were once widely accepted practices to be folly.<br><br>We are at the brink of a new renaissance. Everything will change by degrees, some things to an extreme. This change will be welcome, once the truth is understood, to those who have toiled and suffered under the old way - and unwelcome to those who profit from corruption and iniquity.<br><br>Rules, be they pertaining to mental health, driving a car, or general conduct of individuals, can never result in greater net freedom.<br><br>To move forward, we must learn to be free, to coexist with respect and honor - because honor is the very foundation of our civilization. We live in an honor system and peace can only be found through mutual agreement, or not at all.<br></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,68,'whitehot robot','the rabbit hole of mental illness','',0,0,'#philosophy #mentalhealth #psychology'),(600022,'<div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/27vYZM.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; font-family: courier; line-height:1.4em;text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #88ffff\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 30px;\"><center>On the Question of Consent\'s Validity in Trauma Victims</center></span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\">Under normal, healthy circumstances, the \"appropriateness\" of sex between any consenting parties, may be determined by their legitimate consent itself (defined below). However, in some cases, victims of trauma may have unhealthy, unnatural drives and behaviors, calling the validity of their \"consent\" into question. E.g. very young children previously abused sexually, who may exhibit inordinate promiscuity, exhibitionism, etc. even before puberty, for reasons other than those arising from instinct and natural development. In these cases, said individuals introduce into the formula, the variables of trauma and dysfunction, rendering what would normally be a natural, biological reaction to sexual maturity, unreliable.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br><br></span><font color=\"#88ffff\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">This situation is akin to examples such as those accommodations&nbsp;required for handicapped persons - accessible bathrooms, ramps, etc. due to their special needs. As in these cases, victims of sexual trauma, of any age, are essentially, handicapped, and like in those special considerations in facilities, the world does not stop, but acknowledges and respects their unique conditions, allowing them to function within a \"normal\" framework, but treats them differently by necessity.</span></font><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br><br></span>Special considerations of sexual trauma victims may include refusal to accept \"consent\", or extra, protective measures to verify and ensure proper maturity by other means. The possibility of someone needing special treatment, must then, be determined by investigation into their background, emotional integrity, sexual normalcy, etc. which is literally the main purpose of the first step of the due process of romantic love - to get to know your lover. \"Is this person safe to love?\" - not just for myself, but for themselves as well.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; Consent: a 4-part device, involving...</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>1) Wherewithal (consciousness, demonstrable).</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>2) Understanding of the central effects of the proposal.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>3) (for written agreements) brevity. Reasonable understandability.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>4) Consent itself, either express or implied.</span><br><br><center>-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,41,'whitehot robot','Consent\'s Validity in Trauma Victims','',0,0,'#psychology #sexuality'),(600023,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/intrepid.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/16FuP5.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; font-family: courier; line-height:1.4em;text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"color: #f82; font-size: 40px;\"><br><br><center>The Good Ship Intrepid</center></span><span style=\"color: #ff8; font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><span style=\"color: #ff8; font-size: 20px;\">A cargo vessel, The Intrepid, was robust, and never once arrived late with its transatlantic deliveries of all kinds of imported goods - clothes, woodcraft, automobiles, and whatever else was contracted by her owners, the Eurofreight Co. to be transported between America and many European countries. Her crew consisted of captain Travis Ellington, first mate Steven Halesburg, and about a dozen stalwart men who changed from journey to journey.</span><span style=\"color: #ff8; font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br><br></span><font color=\"#ff8\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">On one fated crossing, afterhours, the ship\'s crew were enjoying some R&amp;R (rest &amp; relaxation) after a long day of very hard work. They, in their usual manner, were feeling and acting rowdy, playing cards, their spirits plied by libations, when one temporary crew member, known only to the crew as \"the Wolf,\" was caught cheating, having tried a very well known grift while playing poker in a high-stakes round. The other players, irate, stood and had to be held back by those not playing to be kept from assailing the Wolf. Shortly, tempers calmed and the Wolf returned the ill-gotten winnings, but those present regarded him differently henceforth, in spite of his smarmy grin and hand waving.<br></span></font><span style=\"color: #ff8; font-size: 20px;\"><br><span style=\"white-space: pre;\">A few days later, the ship\'s mate, Mr. Halesburg, was doing his rounds when he came to the open door of the Wolf\'s quarters. Peering in h</span>e saw the Wolf sitting at the small table, reading something while eating a banana. In the basket atop the table there was other fresh fruit which wasn\'t too surprising considering that fruit was sold in the ship\'s store, but Halesburg paused, realizing that the crew, having only been aboard for 6 days, was not yet paid - they were paid weekly - and he distinctly remembered Mr. Wolf as complaining of being broke when he came aboard. \"Everything good, Mr. Wolf?\" asked the ship\'s mate. \"Of fine. A lovely day \'tis!\" replied the Wolf. From there, Halesburg went straight to the ship\'s larder and reviewed the printed inventory, which showed, some fruit was missing.<br><br>In the end, Mr. Halesburg did not and could not prove any impropriety on the Wolf\'s part, but his regard for the man had changed, like, by now, had the entire crew\'s.<br><br>Little things like these, and perhaps some bigger things never discovered, continued to occur, until one day, well into their voyage, somewhere in the Atlantic, a storm caused epic waves to roll the ship to and fro atop an angry, restless sea. The crew all worked valiantly to secure the mast and batten down the hatches, when suddenly, toward the starboard railing, 3 crewmembers, including the Wolf, watched as a giant swell of seawater buffeted the ship\'s hull, pouring a deluge of salty brine atop the deck and ultimately, swept the Wolf over the railing. With a desperate grab, he managed to reach the rail with one slippery hand, hanging by one arm outside the ship. The other 2 crew instinctively lunged toward him, being good men and seeing a life in peril and wishing to help on reflex - but at the same time, stopped dead in their tracks. The Wolf, now screaming and twisting in the storm, hanging from one arm still, looked a thing to be pitied. The men looked at each other, then stood in place as another wave took the Wolf to his watery grave.<br><br>An investigation into the disappearance of Mr. Wolf was done by the ship\'s mate, which concluded that he had been a victim of the sea. No one missed him, and for the rest of the voyage, things ran smoothly. The moral of the story is:<br><br><center><u>action</u> can never be \"required,\" justifiably, but sometimes <u>inaction</u> may be.</center><br></span><center>-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,44,'whitehot robot','The Good Ship Intrepid','A salty tale',0,1,'#fiction'),(600024,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/expectations.txt\">click here for an unformatted version<br></a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/1AEE30.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 136, 34); font-size: 40px;\"><center><br><br>On Expectations</center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">On a very basic level, we are often \"expected\" to do things independent of our choosing or agreement. Any action which is <u>required</u>, presupposes that, by definition, action sometimes is <u>necessary</u>&nbsp;- that some actions are important enough to <u>depend on</u> by way of making them <u>mandatory</u>. Examining this assumption shows that there is an auxiliary&nbsp;&nbsp;requirement, if action is <u>ever</u> required, for those actors to be in a state of readiness for said action. That is, we cannot be unconscious, dead, unqualified, etc. in order for any expectation of action to be <u>dependable</u>. Obviously, this is unreasonable, un-enforceable, and unrealistic, because if we are ever in a state of un-readiness, the \"required\" or \"expected\" action becomes <u>undependable</u> (!) making <u>expectation of action</u> in general, unsupportable.</span></font><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br><br></span><font style=\"font-family: courier;\" color=\"#ff8\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Following this logic to its conclusion highlights that many systems are basically flawed, attempting to <u>rely on</u>, in error, actions which are <u>unreliable</u> (except those specifically agreed-to by actors while they remain in a state of readiness).</span></font><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px;\"><br><br>So if action cannot be required, where does that leave us? It means that only <u>inaction</u> may reasonably be required (ideally on individual bases), <u>and</u> that:<br><br><center><span style=\"font-size: 32px;font-weight:900;\">Everyone chooses their own level of involvement</span></center><br><br>\"But wait! What about taxation?\" you ask... Good question. This <u>truth</u> means that taxation becomes optional and upon their <u>agreement to participate</u>, entitles one to the benefits of a system which must then <u>earn their business</u>.<br><br>Forced taxation always, eventually, results in a system that, in a vacuum of incentive or necessity to perform, fails its purpose of serving the public, just as does any public entity.<br><br></span><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,35,'whitehot robot','On Expectations','action can never be \"required,\" justifiably, but sometimes inaction may be.',1,1,'#philosophy #policy #taxation'),(600025,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/end_of_law.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/mvNdD.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 136, 34); font-size: 40px;\"><center><br><br>The End of Law</center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Law, defined here as any system and body of rules and language serving the purpose of enacting justice on behalf of the public, is, as will be hereby proven, self-defeating and ultimately unsustainable due to an inherent self-contradiction.</span></font><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br><br></span><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Law\'s fatal flaw is its own reliance on and requirement of <u>precedent</u> by which future proceedings and decisions of those bound by it, are expected to conform. Simply, <u>precedent</u> and its dependency are in direct opposition to a deeper <u>requirement</u> of any justice system, that of <u>due process</u>.</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">To make laws which blindly and unilaterally proscribe arbitrary events and actions irrespective of circumstances, is literally to dispense with the need for, once the \"illegal\" action is assumed or observed to have happened, any further investigation, establishment of context, and, critically, <u>determination of impropriety</u>. Reducing an action to a question of whether or not it is in violation of some past precedent as stipulated by penal codes, is to make an inappropriate comparison between events which cannot be justifiably compared for the purpose of determining wrongdoing, as they involve very different circumstances, and people, usually, and therefore deserve and require independent, objective evaluation, ergo, due process.</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Allegations of misconduct in any legitimate justice system, <u>must be evaluated without bias</u> from previous, different events and their unique circumstances.</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">On a long enough timeline, given Law\'s self-defeating destiny, the resulting injustices, false arrests &amp; prosecutions, and general failure of its purpose to render justice - Law becomes, essentially, a revocation of liberty of those citizens who are promised via sacred documents, patriotic dogma, and the National Anthem itself (in US), that this is the \"land of the free,\" and who are supposedly guaranteed \"life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness,\" but who receive instead, (or don\'t receive, usually), the long list of things that \"just can\'t be done regardless of context.\"</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Any campaign which stops functioning as advertised will eventually be called for reform or removal - especially those central and necessary to our basic survival.</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Considering alternatives, a superior justice system would be one rooted in and based on agreements. </span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Agreements properly involve: </span></font><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>1) Wherewithal (consciousness, demonstrable).</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>2) Understanding of the central effects of the proposal.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>3) (for written agreements) brevity. Reasonable understandability.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>4) Consent itself, either <u>express or implied</u>.</span><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">...Allegations of misconduct, under such a justice system, become complaints of breach of contract, or failure to secure a contract, for any matter involving property or personal space (mental or physical), finances, etc. before which a questionable action is alleged to have transpired. This system will call upon courts and judges that, upon recognizing legitimate complaints, shall grant full, due process to them with appropriate investigation, establishment of context, and finally an objective determination of impropriety without prejudice or bias arising from past precedent, hearsay, conjecture, circumstantial evidence, etc.</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Liberty is not optional. It is not based on lies, incompetence, or irrelevant precedents. Liberty defines an important part of our world and the collective quality of life of its inhabitants. May \"liberty and justice for all\" become,&nbsp; per the US pledge of allegiance, a reality, and an ideal to strive to uphold, cherish, and be proud of.<br><br><center>\"A society may be judged by how it treats its own criminals.\"<br>- anonymous</center></span></font><br><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,50,'whitehot robot','The End of Law','',0,0,'#law #government'),(600026,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #f04;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/what_girls_like.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/1bmZe9.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: #f00; font-size: 40px;\"><center><br><br>What Girls Like</center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#f46\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">\"Girls,\" defined here as women and young women who have, of their own choosing and natural development, joined the world of dating &amp; romance, generally find the following qualities attractive in \"boys.\"</span></font><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br><br></span><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#f46\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Of course, as human individuals, first and foremost, girls\' romantic <u>preferences</u> necessarily vary from person to person, but as givers of life and all that is needed for it to grow during the first years of infancy, females have evolved to be different in certain \"standard\" ways. To dispel&nbsp;some toxic misconceptions, for many years now, an idea has circulated that men and boys, if interested in a girl romantically, must avoid the \"friend zone.\" Simply, if such a thing even exists, it would be absolutely <u>part of</u> any healthy, romantic relationship. The \"friend zone\" idea arose from two erroneous assumptions, that is: 1) The saying \"let\'s just be friends\" means literally what it says. It does <u>not</u>. This saying is the point of total failure in a romantic endeavor, at which the girl, being decent and kind, chooses to communicate what, following the failure, if anything, is still technically possible between the couple - but pretty much always marks the moment when social separation and <u>other romantic paths</u> can and should be pursued by both parties. So the \"friend zone\" is actually the \"nothing zone,\" for clarity. Also, the friend zone idea 2) was based partly on the expectation, not entirely off-base, that being <u>direct</u> and clear about the intention to eventually have sex, and sex supposedly being a justifiable goal in itself, should be the basis for the proposal, in spirit and verbiage. Again, sex without love, companionship, <u>friendship</u>, trust and openness to building a family, is contrary to nature and evolution</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#f46\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Another wrong idea is that girls always prefer boys who are measured, steady, stable, analytical, or safe. While possibly counterintuitive, girls generally prefer, for very good reasons, risk-takers - those boys who act a bit or a lot, on the impulsive side. This trait, in terms of evolution, commonly signifies a partner who is most apt to successfully <u>provide for</u> the family. After all, who first slays the sabretooth lion, the wild boy who fearlessly hunts it with rocks and sticks, or the one who hides from it, returning to the shelter perhaps with a handful of leaves for dinner? Another quality found in tandem with impulsivity, is <u>openness</u> to love and commitment - a very large risk is presented by the consequences of natural sex as pregnancy, which those boys on the wild side, tend not to fear. In fairness, as girls continue to mature into older women, their interests shift slightly toward rationality and an expectation that a man should, while remaining open to risk-taking, be able to through stability, support her established quality of life. But even in these women, a young girl still notices and is attracted to, wild boys.</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#f46\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Other common things attractive to girls are: health, good instincts and intuition - just knowing what to do and a capacity for leadership - responsiveness to her needs and </span><u style=\"font-size: 20px;\">awareness</u><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"> of her feelings without needing them to be explained (also part of intuition). Handsomeness and fitness of course are factors, but usually girls value, above all else in a boy, intelligence. Intelligence, creativity, humor, adaptability, ability to problem-solve, and just figure things out, is very desirable&nbsp;to girls. Finally, and also very important - sexuality - a boy\'s loving touch and capacity for meeting her needs, responding to her signals, and being selfless in bed, girls adore.</span></font><br><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;color: #f00;\">-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,62,'whitehot robot','What Girls Like','An exploration of typical female romantic interests',0,0,'#romance #psychology'),(600027,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/on_contraception.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/1aiYlV.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 136, 34); font-size: 40px;\"><center>On Contraception</center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><font color=\"#ffff88\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">It is standard dogma to begin drilling into youth, from the very first conversation about \"the birds and the bees,\" to <u>use protection</u>. This guidance, sadly is <u>misguidance</u>. Contraception, or prophylactic, results in, always, a reduction or removal of any need for emotional attachment, which, without risk of pregnancy, involves no reward for becoming emotionally invested in ~this~ person - better to be safe emotionally than possibly hurt, so remaining <u>unattached</u> becomes normal with contraception. Patterns of \"serial monogamy\" and general failure between lovers march in lockstep between these, and couples who use birth control.</span></font><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br><br></span><font color=\"#ffff88\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Sex must accompany an understanding that pregnancy is a distinctly possible outcome. If such is unacceptable, then <u>abstinence</u> is the only <u>natural</u> alternative, at the risk of failed relationships, wasted time &amp; energy, broken hearts, and what becomes ultimately, lustful pursuits.</span></font><br><br><font color=\"#ffff88\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Ours is a society fixated on <u>quantity</u> of life over <u>quality</u>. Women and girls are taught that they have <u>equal</u> roles to men, contrary to nature, and therefore invest <u>decades</u> of their lives gaining education and careers, which in nature, would be time spent as mothers. This disconnect is the basis for why children and families currently have so little quality time, and youth are generally raised without understanding of love, (it being circumvented dually via the absence of mothers and the use of birth control, as described), which results, all of it, in a broken society, broken families, and very unnatural, unhappy lives for those affected.</span></font><br><br><font color=\"#ffff88\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><center>...</center></span></font><br><font color=\"#ffff88\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">For a variety of legitimate reasons, not every romantic encounter can be expected to last a lifetime or result in the building of a family, but generally such should not be ruled out as a possibility, or else sex becomes a foolish gamble.</span></font><br><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,62,'whitehot robot','On Contraception','',0,0,'#contraception #nature'),(600028,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;max-width: 100%;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/janis.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/1SLPYu.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 136, 34); font-size: 40px;\"><center><br></center><center><br></center><center><br></center><center><br></center><center><br></center><center>Would You Rather</center><center><br></center><center><br></center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><div style=\"width: calc(100% - 40px); padding-left: 20px;paddig-right: 20px;\"><ol style=\"line-height: 2em;white-space: normal;\">\n<li style=\"line-height: 1em;padding-bottom: 20px;\">Would you rather know of all the losses resulting from your life choices, lost opportunities, lost property, lost love, lost time &amp; money, etc., or die not knowing?</li>\n<li style=\"line-height: 1em;padding-bottom: 20px;\">WYR be angry or depressed?</li>\n<li style=\"line-height: 1em;padding-bottom: 20px;\">WYR be happy or have the ability to fly?</li>\n<li style=\"line-height: 1em;padding-bottom: 20px;\">WYR have one tiny sliver of cake you could eat, or 100 cakes you could only give away anonymously?</li>\n<li style=\"line-height: 1em;padding-bottom: 20px;\">WYR die young, rich, famous and beautiful, or old, poor, and alone?</li>\n<li style=\"line-height: 1em;padding-bottom: 20px;\">WYR meet the love of your life, or have a soul?</li>\n<li style=\"line-height: 1em;\">WYR, if able, make it rain for 100 years causing biblical floods, or be forced to make all the choices on this page?</li>\n</ol></div><br><center>\"Go on now take it! Take another little piece of my heart now baby... You know you got it if it makes you feel good...\" <br>-Janis Joplin</center><br></span><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br><br><br>-end-</center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,45,'whitehot robot','Would You Rather','',0,0,'#wouldyourather'),(600029,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/modes_of_subsistence.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/22LL3X.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 136, 34); font-size: 40px;\"><center><br><br>Modes of Subsistence</center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px;\"><br></span><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">To revisit the topic of morality surrounding use of animals and their products as food, we have not far to look for truth as to what nature intends for us (and them).</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Consider the great cats of the African plains, and the crocodiles, and myriad creatures whose diets involve insects, rodents, fish - etc. Indeed, the sea is a veritable buffet where creatures line up according to size and simply eat the thing in front of them! So the question becomes, not whether animals <u>should</u>&nbsp;be a food source, but 1) at what point does an intelligent species begin to demonstrate divine compassion by abstaining from or reducing its reliance/indulgence on/in animal products, and 2) does a <a href=\"https://words.rotoblaster.com/post/2w5P\" target=\"_blank\">system of agreement</a> extend unto animals, as <u>should</u> be the basis of law between humans? A possible question #3) Can our <u>technology</u>&nbsp;sustain a global, human lifestyle which elevates us above the need for traditional farms, hunting, etc.?</span></font><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><center><br></center></span></font><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#ffff88\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">The answers to these questions arises from answering a more fundamental question - what alternative(s) are there.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">in TOOL\'s popular track \'<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b2BKKeiYH24\" target=\"_blank\">Disgustipated</a>\' Maynard sings \"this is necessary. life feeds on life.\" A stark, undeniable truth that puts things into perspective. Life indeed, can only subsist on other living things be they plants, animals, etc. and any synthetic alternative would surely be, if even tolerable, totally unnatural. So the final question becomes, \"to what extent can the suffering of living things used as food be minimized without unduly compromising our health and quality of life, and for those creatures we <u>must</u> kill, may any agreement exist to mitigate human culpability?</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">It\'s not impossible to imagine that, means of communication aside for the sake of argument, cows on a farm, for example, may volunteer to give their milk in exchange for an easy lifestyle, all needs provided, safe from predators, and tended after in green, sunny pastures, even, possibly with the understanding that a painless death would mark the conclusion of their service...</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Indeed, such may be the only truly righteous way by which cows may be employed by beings who have relatively unlimited options and power to craft systems of sustenance.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">\"It could happen to you!\" The golden rule, while tempting to apply only to those in our communities, or for the truly aware - to all of humanity, becomes more of a divine legal framework as the boundaries between communities blur, and between species, ultimately. The practice of securing an agreement is the only absolute protection we may have against charges of trespassing, theft, rape, and murder. For review, an <u>agreement</u> is defined by the following:</span><br><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>1) Wherewithal (consciousness, demonstrable).</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>2) Understanding of the central effects of the proposal.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>3) (for written agreements) brevity. Reasonable understandability.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(136, 255, 255); font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\"><br>	</span>4) Consent itself, either <u>express or implied</u>.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Asking cows for milk? Craziness, right? Perhaps not as crazy as it sounds... You might even be surprised by the answer you get!</span><br></font><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,48,'whitehot robot','Modes of Subsistence','',0,0,'#nutrition #meat #vegetarianism '),(600030,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/when_the_aspens_fell.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/EBu8T.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 136, 34); font-size: 40px;\"><center><br><br>When the Aspens Fell</center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br></span><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#6fc\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Kim and her husband, Ted Aspen had 2 children, Molly and Joseph, 9 and 7 years old. The aspens did not consider themselves \"rich,\" but their household income and their estate, was valued in the top 10% of the wealthiest of Americans. They had no want for cars, clothes, toys for the kids, or most any kind of economic freedom. But mysteriously, to the parents, their family struggled with frequent arguments, shouting matches, and most recently, a new current of rebelliousness by Molly and, to a lesser extent, Joseph as well.</span></font><br><br><font face=\"courier\" color=\"#6fc\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Molly was just at that age when she was comfortable staying home alone for several hours, and on occasion had babysat her brother while her parent(s) ran to the store, etc. One day, while Ted and Joseph were away at a soccer meet, Kim was planning a small gathering of friends that evening and realized she needed some things from the store, so she called to Molly, but got no response. Curious, but not worried, after all, their home was protected by a state-of-the-art&nbsp;security and surveillance system, Kim walked into one of the front rooms where she heard the television on, and there she found Molly, sitting on the couch, eating chips from a bag, a big mess of chip-crumbs all over the couch and floor. Kim crossed her arms and said to Molly \"No! You will clean this up right now young lady! And didn\'t you hear me call you?\" Molly just shrugged, not taking her eyes off the TV as she continued to eat chips, ignoring her mother. Kim, now irritated, picked up the remote and pressed the power button. Molly\'s eyes shot daggers at her mother,&nbsp;and she jerked her arm, letting the bag of oily chips fall sideways, spilling chips all over the expensive leather sofa. Kim screamed \"Oh now you\'re in trouble... Go to your room right now!\" And grabbing Molly\'s arm, dragged her into her room, then shut the door. Inside her room, Molly jumped-sat on her bed, grabbed one of her many stuffed animals, held it in front of her face, staring into its eyes, cussed at it, then spat in its face.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Hours later, Ted and Joseph came home. Ted said hi to Kim, kissed her, and the boy went about his own business in his room. Ted asked Kim, \"are we ready for tonight?\" Kim replied \"no. I had trouble with Molly and didn\'t feel comfortable leaving her alone. I need things from the store... Can you be here for a bit?\" Ted nodded and said \"sure, also, it\'s probably nothing, but I got some concerning texts from my work. Something about a merger that\'s been in the works that they couldn\'t disclose until now. There\'s going to be an announcement later today...\" Kim smiled and said \"well, you do such good work for them, I\'m sure it\'ll be something good...\" Then she left for the store and Ted went to the game room to watch sports. He checked the score, then turned his attention to the stack of mail on the coffee table, thumbing through the envelopes until he got to one from his bank. Opening it, he twisted his mouth into a scowl as he said to himself, \"man these guys are crooks with this crappy interest rate.\" Then he picked up his phone and called Oscar, his accountant. Oscar picked up on the second ring \"Oscar here. What\'s up Ted?\" Ted said \"Hey bro. Look I\'ve been over a barrel with Wells Fargo for long enough. I need you to move my account to Case - me and Kim, everything.\" Oscar said \"roger that. Everything. Give me a day to get everything set up at Case, then I\'ll move it all over. How\'s the family doing?\" Ted said \"we\'re great. It\'s good to be a rich data ha ha ha.\" Oscar chuckled and they ended the call. Then Ted turned off the TV and went to take a shower.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">After his shower, Ted stepped out of the huge resort-style shower stall onto a soft, imported shower rug, and began to dry himself with the finest towels they sell at Crate &amp; Barrel. But, instantly alert, he froze when he smelled smoke. Throwing on his pants, he bolted out of the bathroom and instantly his eyes stung as a wall of acrid smoke engulfed him when he opened the bathroom door. Instinctively, he called out loudly \"Molly! Joseph!\" He ran to Joseph\'s room first, finding the boy unaware, playing video games. Ted said \"Come with me now! There\'s a fire!\" Then, with his son in hand he ran to Molly\'s room. She wasn\'t there. Ted again screamed \"Molly!\" Running toward the front of the house, he saw the kitchen and front room totally engulfed in flames. Ted ran with Joseph through the door to the garage where he found Molly at his workbench doing something with a doll. She looked at her dad and brother, noticing the fear in their eyes immediately and dropped her doll. Ted ran up to her and said \"Molly we\'ve got to get out of the house. Follow me now.\" She did. Ted clicked the main garage door opener and the three of them went outside into the bright sunlight and fresh air. Ted, thinking quickly noticed that he\'d left his phone in the house and was about to tell the kids to stay put while he ran in to get it, when Kim suddenly arrived, pulling slowly up in front of their driveway. Her eyes darted from her husband and children to the house which now had dark smoke streaming from vents and flames could be seen through the windows. She just gaped and Ted said \"phone!\" She quickly dialed 911 and by the time the fire department put out the blaze, the house was nearly half destroyed, and quite uninhabitable.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">The police, having interviewed the Aspen\'s, were satisfied that Kim\'s story of leaving the burner on, on her stove, and the oven mitt too close, was probably true, but advised them not to leave town until an investigation was completed. The family then drove downtown to eat&nbsp;and check into a hotel.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">At the La Quinta Inn, Ted inquired about vacancies for a family of four and was told they had one, double-king bedroom available. Ted handed over his debit card and waited while the girl at the counter processed it. She looked up and said \"sir, do you have another card? This one\'s not working.\" Ted blinked, then remembered that he was moving his money, so he smiled and asked the girl to \"hold on\" while he went out to the car. He asked Kim for her phone and called Oscar, who answered \"hey Ted. Got everything switched to Chase. Here\'s you new account numbers. Got a pen?\" Ted said \"thanks buddy, but look, I have an emergency and need...\" but the phone died as he was speaking. Ted asked Kim \"is this thing charged?\" And she said,&nbsp;\"it was probably about dead.\" Now getting nervous, Ted checked his wallet again and noticed there were no other credit cards or other forms of payment. Only $40 cash. Kim also had only a small amount of cash and her Wells Fargo card. The family drove to Jack in the Box to eat lunch and figure out their next move. Ted cursed himself for ever deciding&nbsp;to carry two wallets, this one for the gym being lighter without all his stuff in it.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">That evening, they drove around, arguing and panicking because they had no way to pay for a room or even buy a phone charger now, after buying lunch and dinner for 2 adults and 2 kids. Ted parked on a residential street when it got dark and, tired, they all slept in the car.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">It was some time after midnight and it had gotten very cold, but Ted hesitated to run the engine for worry about running out of gas. All this time the kids had been pretty quiet, but suddenly screamed as a bright light beamed through the car window. It was a policeman who tapped on the glass loudly with the butt of his flashlight. Ted turned the key in the ignition so that he could roll the window down. As soon as the window was rolled down, the cop said, \"everything alright here?\" Shining the bright light onto Kim, then the kids in turn. Ted said \"yes. we\'re just stuck here because our house burned down.\" The cop asked for Ted\'s driver license, registration, and proof of insurance. Ted collected the documents and handed them to the cop, who departed for about 5 minutes. When he returned, he handed Ted back his stuff and said \"sorry to hear about your situation, but this is a Neighborhood Watch Community,&nbsp;and someone complained about people sleeping in a car. You can\'t stay here.\" Ted just blinked, feeling trapped. He said \"ok. understood. sorry for any trouble officer.\" Then the cop went back to his car and waited for Ted to leave. Ted drove back into downtown, tired and hungry, the kids asleep and Kim just staring out her window. Then Ted got an idea.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Checking his fuel, he pulled onto the interstate and headed North. Kim just looked at him, her question not needing to be spoken. Ted said \"Martin\'s hunting cabin.\" Then after a few seconds of silence, Kim said \"really?\" Ted said \"yeah. It\'s vacant, remote, and my brother won\'t mind, given the circumstances - just until we sort everything out. Beats sleeping in the Subaru.\" Kim agreed, reluctantly.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Ted drove 2 hours to the land where the cabin was, adjacent to a large national forest. The land had been in Ted\'s family for 3 generations and&nbsp;was bequeathed to his brother Martin when their dad passed away 5 years ago. Since then, the cabin had been used recreationally for summer trips to the forest and nearby lake. It was modest to say the least. More of a rough shack in the woods than anything fancy.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">The aspens arrived at the cabin just before dawn. Ted got out of the car and stretched. Trying the door, he found it unlocked. Inside, a layer of dust covered a small, square roughhewn&nbsp;wooden table. There were two small bed, and a couple of folded cots with sleeping bags. The larder had a small supply of canned food - soups and chili, some green beans and there was a hotplate, but no electricity. Ted went back outside and found a gasoline generator with half-a-tank of fuel in it. Kim had gotten the sleepy kids out of the car and the first light of dawn was just beginning to show in the Eastern sky, but still, the stars twinkled in the cold morning air. The aspens all went into the cabin and Ted made up the cots. Molly and Kim fell asleep on one of the beds and Joseph crawled into one of the sleeping bags and fell asleep. Ted sat on one of the chairs surrounding the table and processed the events of the last day. After 20 minutes, Ted laid down on the empty bed and the whole family slept until noon.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Waking, hungry, Ted, Kim, Molly, and Joseph went outside and checked out the cabin\'s surroundings. Molly exclaimed that she\'d found some fishing poles and Ted discovered a small seating area behind the cabin with a firepit and chairs and some books in a small cabinet, sheltered from the elements under the cabin\'s roof.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Meeting again inside the cabin, the Aspens had a family discussion. Ted informed them all of the food situation and that they had electricity but&nbsp;must ration it. The kids were actually smiling and said they were starving, so Kim opened a can of chili and with bottles of water from the car, they ate. By the end of lunch, they\'d gone through 4 cans of food, nearly  of all they had, but they were full. Recognizing the need for clean water as their top priority, Ted proposed to journey to the lake with some empty containers to fill and bring back. Then he said goodbye to the kids and kissed his wife and left on foot, headed toward the lake.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">While Ted was gone, Kim began to clean the cabin dusting and using a broom she\'d found. She asked Molly and Joseph to help her and almost fainted when they quickly and eagerly volunteered. The three of them cleaned the small windows, the dishes and sink, made the beds and cots, then went outside to sit in the chairs around the defunct firepit. Kim explored the books in the cabinet, finding some interesting books about birds, fishing, and some fictional novels, also some magazines about hunting that looked very old.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Ted returned with his jugs and bottles all filled with water from the lake, and the kids were happy to see him. He then set about using coffee filters and pans to boil and filter the water. He drank first. It tasted delicious.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">The Aspens stayed at the cabin for a long time, using the generator only 30 minutes each evening to cook and clean dishes. They fished and caught and ate many fish, cooking them over the firepit. The family grew very close, and it was no mystery to Ted and Kim that virtually all of the behavior problems formerly troubling the kids, had vanished. They all worked and played as a unit, fishing, cleaning, reading, and loving. Ted, thinking hard about everything, decided that his error had been in trying to substitute toys and security for meaningful, shared experiences, memories that they would all cherish for their whole lives.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Eventually, the gasoline ran out, which was probably good timing as autumn was well underway and nights were getting quite chilly. So one day, several months after their arrival at the cabin, the Aspens drove back to civilization, contacted the right people, and resumed their lives of luxury, but all were forever changed by the humble, shared experience they\'d had. And from then on, Ted and Kim gave no more toys as gifts to Molly and Joseph, rather as a family they travelled and explored and marveled at the beauty of the world - it\'s cities, nature and widely varied peoples, together. And they were happy. Molly and Joseph grew up better for all these experiences and passed this wisdom on to their own children, who quickly forgot it... Words, after all, are temporary. But </span><u style=\"font-size: 20px;\">their</u><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"> children, troubled by their families\' superficialities, ended up having similar epiphanies to those in this story - and on the cycle goes.</span><br></font><br><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,52,'whitehot robot','When the Aspens Fell','A short story',0,0,'#fiction #materialism'),(600031,'<div style=\"text-align:left;padding:10px;color:green;\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">Three\nLaments<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">I: <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">I should have told him<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">I loved him with enough passion<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">to warm us both forever <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">but the words never came<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">so he left<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">II:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">I may never find enough time to<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">experience everything<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">I dream of<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">III:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">The leaves that blow off the trees<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">in an Autumn color parade<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">remind me of life length <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">begging me to notice everything<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">the world sends me<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Truetypewriter PolyglOTT&quot;,serif\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I\nrealize I have missed so much<o:p></o:p></span></p></div><div style=\"text-align:left;padding:10px;color:green;\"><br>\n</div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',11,4,'jenifer','Three Laments','Poetry',1,0,'#sharingwithmyHusband'),(600032,'','2022-04-09 14:27:01',11,2,'jenifer','','',1,0,''),(600033,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/on_justification_and_reason.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/257Guj.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ff8\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 136, 34); font-size: 40px;\"><center><br></center><center><br></center><center><br></center><center><br></center><center>On Justification and Reason</center><br><br></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br></span><font color=\"#ff6\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">\"The end justifies the means,\" a famous saying calling into question the ethical/moral latitude of actions underneath a supposedly just umbrella, states that if the result is benevolent, the entire process is justified. This brutal formula is lacking a key consideration, the absence of which renders it incomplete and unable to support any claim of true morality.</span></font><br><br><font color=\"#ff6\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">The completeness of logic can make or break any formula, and when morality is its basis, the effects can be disastrous for many. <u>Constraints</u>, those things, actions, or behaviors that cannot enter into a formula (defined specifically or in terms of generalities),&nbsp;<u>must </u>cover and prohibit any subpart of a process from transgressing into moral territory which, irrespective of the \"ends,\" cannot independently be justified. So the <u>complete</u> true formula becomes:</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 30px;\"><center>The end justifies, <b>within established constraints</b>, the means.</center></span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">...thereby burdening the designer with the responsibility to consider wayward, potentially harmful effects caused by their so-called benevolent solution, and for which they must be answerable.</span><br></font><br><br><br><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,38,'whitehot robot','On Justification and Reason','',0,0,'#philosophy'),(600034,'<div style=\"position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/competitions_domain.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/HvCyf.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;\" #ace\"=\"\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fa8; font-size: 40px;\"><center><br></center><center><br></center><center>Competition\'s Domain</center><br></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br></span><font color=\"#ace\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Many subjects or games lend themselves naturally to competition, whereas many do not. The dividing line between these categories is surprisingly clear and easy to define.</span></font><br><br><font color=\"#ace\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">In mathematics, a \"domain\" is the range of possible values returned by a function. To borrow this concept, the domain of competition is only those subjects or games in which the competitors may be evaluated on a strictly linear basis. A few examples, chess, checkers, poker, etc. have one winner and one or more losers based on a rigidly defined set of rules that boil down to a linear equation. Checkers, for example, concludes when one player captures the last of their opponent\'s pieces, whereas in poker, a numerical comparison of each player\'s hand-values places each of them on a linear (1-dimensional) graph, the top player being the winner, etc. These linear-type games, sports, races, etc. all have 1-dimensional, linear structures to determine the winner. But, some subjects, like beauty, art, music, literature, etc. are multidimensional and any attempt at linear competition becomes either meaningless or must truncate a dimension to make a linear analysis possible. Take a beauty contest for example, the entrants may all be beautiful, but the judges must decide which is <u>most</u>&nbsp;beautiful, frankly, a matter of opinion at best, and hardly quantifiable. But beauty exists and we all know it when we see it, so why can\'t it be quantified?</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Beauty, art, etc. and all multidimensional subjects have non-linear domains - that is, while we all recognize the basic \"axis\" of beauty, there exists a second dimension - that of individual preference, which extends from our own unique genders, sexual orientations, ethnicities, and formative experiences most importantly. This secondary dimension is the framework which guides, in the example of beauty, the primary dimension by way of evolution. Separately, and a subject for a different text, is the granular nature of evolution, occurring not on the level of life as a whole, nor as species, but individually, every time a creature or plant reproduces.<br><br>So an art or music competition, like a beauty contest, must disclaim that any \"victors\" are such only insofar as the judges evaluated them with <u>favoritism</u>.<br><br>There can be no objective \"most beautiful person,\" or \"best song,\" or \"most attractive art piece\" because, simply, such an analysis is mathematically impossible due to the complex nature of these and many other things.</span></font><br><br><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:01',145,56,'whitehot robot','Competition\'s Domain','',0,0,'#ph'),(600035,'<div style=\"line-height: 1.4em;position: absolute;margin: 20px;background-color: #408;border-radius: 10px;cursor: pointer; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #0f4;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cantelope.org/objective_truth_and_its_dependence_on_conceptual_specificity.txt\">click here for an unformatted version</a></div><div style=\"padding: 20px; background-image: url(&quot;https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/1620Dk.jpg&quot;); background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover; line-height: 1.4em; text-shadow: rgb(0, 0, 0) 2px 2px 2px; text-align: justify;font-family:courier;\"><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fa8; font-size: 40px;\"><center><br></center><center><br></center><center>Objective Truth &amp; its Dependence on Conceptual Specificity</center></span><span style=\"font-family: courier; color: rgb(255, 255, 136); font-size: 20px; white-space: pre;\"><br></span><font color=\"#afc\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Natural languages, having evolved organically over the ages, while indispensable&nbsp;to civilization, often give rise to disagreement and conflict over meaning and truth container therein.</span></font><br><br><font color=\"#afc\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Conveniently, mathematics, philosophy, and scientific languages make a point of <u>disambiguating</u> their terminology so as to enable and streamline logical reasoning. Natural languages... not so much!</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Words are mere symbols - of things, properties, qualities, and some glue to make it all flow so as to be understood. But as symbols, words necessarily simplify, group, conceptualize, and represent subjects with a great deal of ambiguity, making agreement on definition, scope, etc., a requirement before comprehension and communication is achievable. Fortunately, most of the time, <u>context</u>&nbsp;informs us, intuitively as to the <u>intended</u> scope and meaning of language, but not always.<br><br>Truth wholly depends on evaluation of <u>the agreed-upon meaning</u>&nbsp;of elements which must be stripped of any ambiguity before objective analysis becomes possible. For some things, this is trivial with the help of math and other non-subjective tools. For example, the word \"blue\" may conjure an image in mind, and a color between blue and something else may cause disagreement between those asked if it is \"blue,\" but a solution exists to disambiguate and <u>concretely </u>define \"blue\"... That is, to establish an <u>objective</u> system of evaluation (a neutral computer program attached to a camera, for example), and bind those surveyed to an \"agreement to arbitrate\" via said program, whereby eliminating all possibility of disagreement.<br><br>But what of non-quantifiable, intangible, or ineffible subjects? Perhaps some things can never be concretely defined to a point of agreeability and disambiguation that may support objective analysis... Things like dignity, purpose, happiness, etc. For these things, arguably, there can be no universal truth beyond that which exists individually as matters of opinion.<br><br>The strongest foundation is always that which is based upon facts, truth being the only thing in the universe which cannot be destroyed. So it follows that the most prudent environment must <u>maximize</u> opportunities to define, disambiguate, and <u>agree upon</u>&nbsp;subjects of controversy. A desire to communicate and understand each other and to involve <u>context</u> inasmuch&nbsp; as possible underlies this end. May the light of truth guide us out of darkness and into a happier, more dignified future for all.</span></font><br><br><br><center style=\"font-family: courier;\">-end-</center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"font-family: courier;\"><br></center></div>','2022-04-09 14:27:02',145,63,'whitehot robot','Objective Truth & its Dependence on Conceptual Specificity','',0,0,'#philosophy'),(600036,'<div>tz1eQkPob5jLEVvJDzA2rJqNcRxY9bGG8oJn</div><div>depend blush change clog tomato unlock runway letter rubber absent child gas</div>','2022-04-09 20:23:59',145,23,'whitehot robot','plorg wallet (whitehot robot)','',1,0,''),(600037,'<div style=\"line-height:1.2em;padding:20px;border:1px solid transparent;text-align: justify;color: #ffc;font-family: courier;max-width: 800px;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n<br><center><br></center><center>Creative Sensitivity and Holy Communion<br><br></center><center><br></center>Practicing Buddhist monks may appear to outsiders, to spend questionable amounts of time in deep meditation. Their routines literally involve fulltime tranquility and mental isolation, morning noon and night. To some, this devotion to piety and solitude borders on tedium. But to the monks, there can be no more fulfilling way to spend their time.<br><br>It is in the space of total isolation where, eventually, a relationship with God begins to form. Not, as many expect, in busy church sanctuaries or bustling social venues. The substance of Communion is the most private and personal spiritual connection one can have with the raw energy of synthesis and creation. It is where muses originate and it exists on a one-to-one basis between the participant and the Universe.<br><br>In \"Before Night Falls\", a movie about the famed poet Reinaldo Arenas, his character is followed through life from the humblest beginnings in rural Cuba to his eventual death in a rough-shod apartment where a friend\'s compassion led to his assisted euthanasia. Notably, Arenas\' \"sensitivity\" as a poet arose, in his own opinion, from the complete and extreme, abject poverty and family dysfunction of his childhood. His mother was basically a wild native, living in the jungles of Cuba and his father was absent for much of his life due to his mother\'s instability. The isolation and vast amounts of time Arenas spent in deep contemplation and (forced) meditation surely contributed to the development of his poetic prowess.<br><br>In the movie \"Donnie Darko\", a skilled teacher is conducting a thought experiment in Donnie\'s high school class, whereby students must write about and discuss new inventions of their own. One student comes up with the idea of a sort of infant virtual reality headset which, as they describe, conveys imagery and content to the child. Part of the exercise is to anticipate the effects of ideas and teach/learn to plan for them. The teacher points out that possibly, infants need darkness. That darkness may be necessary as part of the natural development of babies. The point echoes that development of cognitive abilities, creativity, and mental stability depends on, to a large extent, absence of stimuli and long periods of peaceful introspection, beginning, likely, before birth. Can any environment be more supremely meditative than mother\'s womb?<br><br>Whether a real connection with the divine can exist or if it is merely imagined or symbolic, isolation, privacy, peace and introspection are necessary for the development of creative sensitivity.<br><br><br><center>-end-</center><br><br></div>','2022-04-09 21:05:09',145,73,'whitehot robot','Creative Sensitivity & Holy Communion','the source of creativity',0,0,'#psychology #meditation'),(600038,'<div style=\"line-height: 1.2em; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid transparent; text-align: justify; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n<br><center style=\"color: #4f8; font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"\"><font color=\"#4f8\" face=\"courier\">Complexity &amp; the Limits of Human Cognition</font><br></center><center style=\"color: #4f8; font-family: courier;\"><br></center><center style=\"color: #4f8; font-family: courier;\"><br></center><font color=\"#4f8\" face=\"courier\">The unaided mind may never fully grasp reality in full-detail. Being largely symbolic (language-based), human thought necessarily groups things, much to the annoyance of thinkers who may wish for truly accurate comprehension of their environments. Words, as symbols, provide means by which we may exemplify and limit the conceptual scope. But as symbols, words can never be the things themselves. However deeply one may penetrate into layers of complexity, in spite of the discovery of successively, more-numerous contingencies, the answer of \"yes &amp; no, depending on...\" continues to arise. This elusiveness of answerability underlies all questions relating to real* phenomena. Absolute qualities like \"good\", \"bad\", etc. exist only relative to some given context, which is too frequently and inappropriately assumed to be true and pertinent, without verification of facts. Indeed, the rabbit hole of fact checking often yields more questions that it can answer.</font><br><br><font color=\"#4f8\" face=\"courier\">But all is well for they who learn that question need not be answer to exhaustion, rather only to sufficiency, which still may require superhuman effort to explore all aforementioned contingencies until the primary inquiry stands answered by a reasonably confident support. The danger of course is rushing to judgement, jumping to conclusions, or compartmentalizing beliefs. Truth, as reality, exists as a single, contiguous entity. Never does it contradict itself, nor is it found in degrees. This truth (of truth!) comprises the most valuable tool for apprehending answers to complex questions. Delving into dependencies and nested contingencies becomes trivial upon a broad, truthful base (knowledge), for every answer to emergent questions must never contradict any previous conclusion. In short, the more one knows, the more (and faster) one can learn, hence the vital necessity of <u>good</u> education. To learn how to think is precursor to thinking. Answering questions to sufficiency is the basis for why it is best to err on the side of optimism, rather than caution, lest one become a crazy tyrant. Caution is the sibling of fear, and in a heart without fear, evil can find no purchase.</font></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><font color=\"#44ff88\" face=\"courier\">&nbsp; *\"real\", as opposed to theoretical as in science &amp; mathematics</font><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 255, 136); font-family: courier;\">.</span></div><div style=\"line-height: 1.2em; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid transparent; text-align: justify; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"><br><center style=\"color: #4f8; font-family: courier;\">-end-</center><br><br></div>','2022-04-11 17:05:27',145,81,'whitehot robot','Complexity & the Limits of Human Cognition','',0,0,'#neurology'),(600039,'<div style=\"white-space:pre;color:#fff;text-align: left;font-family:courier;padding: 50px;\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n  &lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;style&gt;\n      body, html{\n        overflow: hidden;\n        background: #000;\n        height: 100vh;\n      }\n      #pic{\n        background-image: url(827EM.jpg);\n        background-size: contain;\n        background-repeat: no-repeat;\n        background-position: center center;\n        width: 100%;\n        height: calc(100% - 40px);\n        margin: 20px;\n      }\n    &lt;/style&gt;\n  &lt;/head&gt;\n  &lt;body&gt;\n    &lt;div id=\"pic\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;script&gt;\n      mp3=new Audio()\n      playing=false\n      mp3.loop = true\n      mp3.src=\'9f1b261a1a6530b71e70b03c09c3d013.MP3\'\n      window.onclick=()=&gt;{\n        if(!playing)mp3.play(), playing=true\n      }\n      mp3.play()\n    &lt;/script&gt;\n  &lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</div>\n','2022-04-11 22:48:52',145,74,'whitehot robot','sample markup for image + audio on plorg.net','',0,0,''),(600040,'<div style=\"line-height:1.2em;padding:20px;border:1px solid transparent;text-align: justify;color: #ffc;font-family: courier;max-width: 800px;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n<br><center><br></center><center>understanding symbols - a parable<br><br></center><center><br></center>In Pasteur Elementary School, performance was graded by a simple system. An average work received a yellow star. A perfect work, a red star, and a lacking work, a blue star. As children do there were play-yard taunts and jeers like \"Alice doesn\'t know where we are, because she only gets the blue star!\" and so on. One day the parents rallied for the removal of the blue star from the grading system and the school obliged.<br><br>An orange star took the place of the blue, but this resulted in new jeers \"he can\'t spell, poor dumb George, that is why his star is orange!\"<br><br>Confounded, the school and teachers had a meeting where it was decided that symbols weren\'t the problem, rather the cruelty of some children, and the reluctance of everyone to accept that bad things like poor performance and some cruelty are unavoidable.<br><br><br><center>-end-</center><br><br></div>','2022-04-14 03:56:23',145,84,'whitehot robot','understanding symbols - a parable','',0,0,'#wisdom'),(600041,'<div style=\"line-height:1.2em;padding:20px;border:1px solid transparent;text-align: justify;color: #ffc;font-family: courier;max-width: 800px;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n<br><center><br></center><center>gender fixation in the entertainment industry<br><br></center><center><br></center>For countless years the show business branch of the women\'s liberation movement has bemoaned undue fixation on artist/performer gender identity, citing unfair bias and irrelevancy of gender differentiation.<br><br>The fact of womanhood or other, is not only significant, but the crux of marketability of modern media due to measurable, predictable biological factors that absolutely separate females from males in terms of behavior patterns in nature, and in trends of marketability.<br><br>Modern society is one ever on the hunt for any and every example of discrimination, demonizing it as though discrimination (sexual or otherwise) were an optional, unsavory thing. When in fact discrimination is the basis for every form of quality control. Without discrimination, individuality loses meaning and the quality of everything becomes unmeasurable.<br><br>The problem of sexual discrimination in entertainment, as usual, is too often mis-identified as something it\'s not, misogyny in this case. The problem is actually rooted not in discrimination, but the spirit and attitudes of those involved. The essence of entertainment (and every type of human interaction) depends wholly on the sentiment, respect, and ultimate effects of the words and actions of players. For example, in business, courtship, etc. if amorous advances are made in obnoxious, offensive ways, the recipient may justifiably complain about sexual harassment or unfair sexual discrimination. But the EXACT SAME ACTIONS effected by someone else in a respectful, complimentary spirit, will likely and correctly be warmly received.<br><br>An accurate complaint is as important as addressing complaints to the right people (which is seldom ~everyone~ at large). The complaint of sexual discrimination in entertainment is usually, in fact a complaint of offensive objectification, disrespect, and general dissatisfaction with the spirit and nature of the people at whom the complaints are aimed, not discrimination or gender acknowledgement per se.</div><div style=\"line-height:1.2em;padding:20px;border:1px solid transparent;text-align: justify;color: #ffc;font-family: courier;max-width: 800px;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"><center>-end-</center><br><br></div>','2022-04-18 19:41:31',145,87,'whitehot robot','gender fixation in the entertainment industry','',0,0,'#sociology #sexism #misogyny'),(600042