 10:10:31',145,28,'whitehot robot','Airgap xtz','',1,0,''),(600051,'<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">The Highest Crimes</span></font><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">As history confirms, a languishing civilization is marked by the predictable transition from a handful of regulations intended to keep the peace, to volumes of laws intended to protect the state. It becomes more a crime to disagree with or disrespect the ruling class, than to murder members of the working class. This stage of corruption is invariably the harbinger of revolution, as the weight of \"elite\" parasites begins to crush those upon whom they subsist, rendering chaos, civil unrest, and social imbalance across the board. Eventually the injustice and oppression can no longer be concealed behind clever language or propaganda, and the myriad failures of the governing to perform as such, are exposed.</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">American Founding Father Thomas Jefferson said, \"Dissent is the highest form of patriotism,\" speaking of America\'s independence from a cruel and corrupt English government which sought through military force to prevent Her separation from The Crown. Many of the early ideals and policies of the United States were rooted in deep philosophical truth and wisdom. But some were not, like allowing importation of slaves, and embracing a system of pure economic competition in which every person and business became adversaries. These shortsighted errors doomed a mighty young nation to perpetual civil strife, extreme economic disparity, and an unsupportable burden on the government itself to manage the forces unleashed by capitalism.</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">The challenge of extracting positive content from mixed or otherwise harmful/negative content eludes many people. But in spite of its failures, the documents and ideas which formed the cornerstones of the US carried tremendous experience and knowledge from Europe and its great thinkers. The ideas that liberty and God are connected, for example, while all but forgotten now, were the seeds from which everything great eventually grew. Examining this concept, it becomes clear that liberty is the natural reward for good decisions. That is, bad behavior results in (and is defined by) loss of liberty. But conversely and more importantly, good (or righteous) behavior is rewarded by gains in liberty, eventually culminating in perfect liberty, known as a state of nature, or anarchy. Any society\'s performance can be measured by how little or how much liberty its average citizens enjoy. How many or how few laws are imposed on its people, and ultimately, how much or how little management (or governance) is required. A parallel yardstick for society\'s performance is how it treats its less-fortunate (defined by itself).</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">With these truths, it becomes trivial to measure and respond to the forces that affect all members of society. And upon viewing ours through this lens, what can be seen?</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><center>-end-</center><center><br></center></div>','2022-05-17 17:29:06',145,106,'whitehot robot','The Highest Crimes','',0,0,''),(600052,'<br>1-707-703-1983','2022-05-17 19:53:33',145,25,'whitehot robot','MyFax Number','',1,0,''),(600053,'tz1V2xhjbZsZ2Zx86zcuajdqJfChXdi51rB1&nbsp;\n','2022-05-18 00:37:40',145,28,'whitehot robot','temple addy xtz tezos','',1,0,''),(600054,'0x63e696a28EF9A6E91840F6fEc86AFA0d08DA9FEc&nbsp;','2022-05-18 01:47:09',145,18,'whitehot robot','Eth metamask','',1,0,''),(600055,'<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Not Being Ridiculous</span></font><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">Everyone has heard \"what doesn\'t kill you makes you stronger.\" But even the feebleminded need not think long for contrary examples, like losing a limb etc. While gain sometimes involves figurative pain, many confuse this with literal pain, inviting and expecting it into their lives.</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">While hardship and pressure can surely build character, it is equally important for mental health and keeping in touch with human bases, to figuratively stop and smell the roses, to indulge within moderation, appetites for simple things which may not be strictly necessary.</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">Life is not about punching oneself in the head. To lose sight of the prize, that is, for most, health and happiness, and to ignore reasonable opportunities to partake in these is to lose the path and miss the point of being alive.</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><center>-end-</center><center><br></center></div>','2022-05-19 00:43:47',145,88,'whitehot robot','Not Being Ridiculous','',0,0,''),(600056,'<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Cause and Effect Reciprocity</span></font><br></div><div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; margin: 10px;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Which came first the chicken or the egg? Well, they each depend on each other, embodying the concept of&nbsp;</span></font><i style=\"\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">cause-and-effect&nbsp;reciprocity</span></font></i><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">.</span></font></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">Also known as self-reinforcing patterns, self-fulfilling prophecies, or the Law of Attraction, the effects of many events and behaviors have a symbiotic feedback relationship with their own causes.</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\">An example is the frustration couples sometimes experience during disagreements. What begins as a miscommunication can escalate into a full-blown row, which soon has nothing to do with the original disagreement but the row itself and the inability of the parties to understand and respond in a desirable way. The effect of the frustration feeds back into its own cause, creating a loop. These patterns once recognized can be harnessed for good, or stymied once understood, as in the above example.</div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;font-family: courier; font-size: 20px;line-height: 1em;color: white;margin: 10px;\"><center>-end-</center><center><br></center></div>','2022-05-19 22:54:06',145,90,'whitehot robot','Cause and Effect Reciprocity','',0,0,''),(600057,'tz1iR175xfQhugguQYSsApWoCeqPYvp1hnmC<br>present claw buddy baby lawn wrist warfare distance thank citizen album rabbit','2022-05-26 18:35:12',145,26,'whitehot robot','whitehot2 plorg wallet xtz','',1,0,''),(6000