ustify;\">In consideration of this, a 5th requirement is patently necessary.<br>\n</div><div style=\"margin: 20px; font-family: courier;color: #fff;text-align: justify;\">5) All considerations factoring into consent must be undivided, involving only the INDIVIDUALS in question.</div><div style=\"margin: 20px; font-family: courier;color: #fff;text-align: center;\"><br></div><div style=\"margin: 20px; font-family: courier;color: #fff;text-align: center;\">-end-</div><div style=\"margin: 20px; font-family: courier;color: #fff;text-align: center;\"><br></div>','2022-06-25 03:53:36',145,60,'whitehot robot','the evolution of consent','',0,0,'#morality #sexuality #psychology'),(600067,'<a href=\"https://www.sharedrop.io/rooms/d9e21554-0b60-474d-93c5-0331576d4377\">https://www.sharedrop.io/rooms/d9e21554-0b60-474d-93c5-0331576d4377</a>','2022-06-26 18:37:15',145,11,'whitehot robot','','',1,0,''),(600068,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff;margin:20px;text-align: justify;\">So much is taken for granted by modern composers, inventors, and everyone who benefits from the centuries of backbreaking research that is the foundation of modern practice. For example, if tasked with building a cell phone or even a bicycle from scratch (financial barriers notwithstanding), most people would be at a loss, which should call into question their entitlement to use these things. Do not aspects of judgement, understanding, and responsibility normally accompany the wherewithal to invent things, and can we assume that end users need never have them? ...</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff;margin:20px;text-align: justify;\">Seemingly innocuous, the technology of music theory, its structure and capacity for creating emotions and conveying ideas, is among the most subtly powerful and potentially dangerous of technologies. But before this text is mistaken as a vote for censorship, the subject here is specifically the chords, intervals, and progressions of the Western Scale.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff;margin:20px;text-align: justify;\">The persons involved in the design of the 12-note scale used by virtually all Western (not Asian or middle Eastern) music, are not relevant, nor necessarily known. Much of our \"history\" is fabricated to suit those in power at the time of its writing and is therefore unreliable and often inaccurate. But this 12-note design (C, C#/D, D, D#/E, E, F, F#/G, G, G#/A, A, A#, B, B), contains the frequencies which resonate in the human brain as basic warmth, light &amp; happiness, or cooler sadness &amp; darkness. These flavors are called major and minor chords, respectively.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff;margin:20px;text-align: justify;\">Without getting too technical (this is not a technical paper), the nature of a chord and its emotional charge is inverted by the placement of the 3rd interval, major if placed 4 steps above the key, or minor if \"diminished\", placed 3 steps above the key. Of course, traditional music typically involves not just one chord, but \"chord progressions\" which may involve major and minor scales, but for a given position in a song, the scale determines the feeling, warm or cool, at that place. The amazing thing is how these intervals were discovered and implemented for every orchestral instrument (save certain percussion instruments) uniformly and so effectively.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff;margin:20px;text-align: justify;\">With respect to all the various embellishments, improvisations, and clever adaptations by augmenting or diminishing various notes, the emotional character of a piece all hinges on the third interval, without which (and often it is absent intentionally), the listener remains unsure of the song\'s disposition, fortuitous or foreboding.<br>\n</div>','2022-07-13 15:40:17',145,58,'whitehot robot','music as a vehicle for emotions','',0,0,'#music #theory'),(600069,'<br><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: CoinbaseSans, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Fira Sans&quot;, &quot;Droid Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: start;\">tz1QtMB5aGPmLEwy8nqaV7ee6zBwV7YTHoGh</span><br>','2022-07-14 00:33:19',145,12,'whitehot robot','xtz srmcgann coinbase advanced','',1,0,''),(600070,'<br><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"CoinbaseSans, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, Fira Sans, Droid Sans, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif\">TZ1X6UVNQDFQMXNMMHPCESDKNPJBCUGIE1AQ</font><br>','2022-07-14 00:35:38',145,12,'whitehot robot','xtz payway.dweet coinbase advanced','',1,0,''),(600071,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px; text-align: justify;font-size: 20px;line-height:1em;\"><center><br></center><center>Affirmative Action</center><center><br></center></div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px; text-align: justify;font-size: 20px;line-height:1em;\">\nAffirmative action, the policies and laws for employment in many places aimed at combatting racial discrimination, more aptly called affirmative RE-action, is based on the assumption and expectation that racial discrimination is present and a factor in employment screening. This assumption is sometimes correct, and sometimes not, but a better approach to eliminate unfair discrimination would be implementation of a double-blind screening / testing process whereby applicants\' race could not be considered as a deciding factor.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px; text-align: justify;font-size: 20px;line-height:1em;\">This approach differs in 2 critical ways from Affirmative Action, in that employers\' abilities to maintain a quality of staff is preserved, versus forcing them to employ someone of a particular race in order to fulfill a quota to the exclusion of a possibly better qualified candidate. Secondly, The only justification for Affirmative Action is the aforementioned assumption of racist hiring practices, which is as much discriminatory against employers as said practices would be of applicants.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px; text-align: justify;font-size: 20px;line-height:1em;\">Ultimately, and invariably, reactions to problems like racial discrimination by way of laws, restrictions, penalties, and forced hiring of anyone, results in a loss of quality of personnel, stolen autonomy by policy makers from employers, a failure to serve the purpose of Affirmative Action itself (no employer can employ representatives from EVERY race), and, an enforcement against companies of being able to ensure their own best chances of success.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px; text-align: justify;font-size: 20px;line-height:1em;\">With that said, racism, unfair discrimination (not all discrimination), and violation of EQUAL OPPORTUNITY are very real challenges for everyone. Hiring practices will never be completely fair, but this problem stems from, like many others, a broken economic system where everyone must \"coin up\" or die.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px; text-align: justify;font-size: 20px;line-height:1em;\">Upon close examination, people are never equal, nor can they be. This reality must be acknowledged and form the basis of every expectation regarding employment and support for community members which may be less or un-qualified for work.<br>\n</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px; text-align: justify;font-size: 20px;line-height:1em;\"><center>end</center></div>','2022-07-17 17:50:29',145,64,'whitehot robot','Affirmative Action','',0,0,''),(600072,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; text-align: center; margin: 20px; line-height: 1em;font-size: 20px;\">\nTrade Secrets</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; text-align: justify; margin: 20px; line-height: 1em;font-size: 20px;\">For hundreds of years or more, among the unquestioned business practices of the West are companies\' rights and prerogative to keep trade secrets. As with any widespread assumption, there are at least edge and corner cases where such practices fall squarely out of justification, and into criminal activity.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; text-align: justify; margin: 20px; line-height: 1em;font-size: 20px;\">Upon close inspection, the character of a practice, custom, or behavior can be predicted based on its motives. Are they honorable, necessary, and prudent? Or are they deceptive, manipulative, and self-serving? Trade secrets and secrets of any kind are justifiable only in the presence of substantial, measurable danger to the health and safety of a person or business. Otherwise, secrets form deception by way of omission. Herein lies the great folly of public acceptance of secrets as normal, necessary practice in business and government. That is, just because something has been the common way, doesn\'t mean it is the right way, or is it justified.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; text-align: justify; margin: 20px; line-height: 1em;font-size: 20px;\">In fairness, examining trade secrets from both perspectives (pro and con), helps to establish their legitimacy. For example, it is a trade secret among manufacturers of disposable razors that the metal used in their blades is very precisely and scientifically softened with an alloy composition so as to ensure that they will be quickly disposed of. What if I told you that modern engineering could easily make a disposable razor for cheap that lasted virtually forever?</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; text-align: justify; margin: 20px; line-height: 1em;font-size: 20px;\">We find that every instance of corporate trade secrets follows suit to this example, with a departure into the universe of Intellectual Property being the epitome of rhetoric in favor of trade secrets. \"How can our inventors be paid if their work is stolen?\" This concern has little if any substance or merit nowadays in that 1) almost every invention is derivative of another, 2) concerning the digitization of information, enforcement of patents and copyright has become impossible, and 3) the expectation of ownership of an idea and payment for its use is another unquestioned assumption, like that trade secrets are automatically great. The idea that an invention can or should belong to the inventor is a REACTION to the condition of capitalism that demands everyone work at figurative gunpoint. The underlying reality is that reconciliation of debt from someone taking credit for an idea or benefitting from its implementation, cannot be legislated. At the end of the day, this too is an honor system and our best hope is to encourage people to, when able, contribute to and compensate those from whose work they benefit.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; text-align: justify; margin: 20px; line-height: 1em;font-size: 20px;\">Payment for services is always optional, especially when those services address vital necessities. A final incorrect, widespread assumption is that payment MUST be rendered for things like food, shelter, clothing, and taxes. Providing for all basic human needs is easily within the sphere of possibility when resources are not stolen, squandered, or secretly traded between conspiratorial, parasitic corporations and government entities.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; text-align: center; margin: 20px; line-height: 1em;font-size: 20px;\">end<br>\n</div>','2022-07-18 12:57:50',145,76,'whitehot robot','Trade Secrets','',0,0,''),(600073,'<font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"CoinbaseSans, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, Fira Sans, Droid Sans, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif\" style=\"text-align: start;\">0xF41c3ed1bd1C7cb698D6a7155521596C24857Ba3 (POLYGON)&nbsp;</font><br style=\"text-align: start;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"CoinbaseSans, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, Fira Sans, Droid Sans, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif\" style=\"text-align: start;\">0x7Ae596D4d98e27F3f8C6da152017a9712C802F99 (ERC20)</font><br>','2022-07-22 17:40:25',145,15,'whitehot robot','polygon matic coinbase payway.dweet','',1,0,''),(600074,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; font-size: 20px\">\n<center>domination and respect</center><br>\nA recurring theme in many self-proclaimed \"evil\" story lines, is the subversion of choices of another. Intuitively, most people understand that the right, proper thing is to maximize the liberty of others. In practice this resembles allowing them to make their own decisions in appearance, spirit, and reality.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; font-size: 20px\">But unfortunately, in authoritarian atmospheres one is expected to follow the rules set by a superior authority. Questioning the relevancy of the rules or the authority\'s qualifications is usually punished, as is defying the rules. Systems emerge for the indoctrination of \"managers\", new authority figures to make decisions for the \"less-qualified\", whereby the will of said managers is superimposed over that of their \"inferiors\".</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; font-size: 20px\">This practice of actively disabling the power and autonomy of individuals in lieu of a centralized code of conduct, when relied upon as a standard accepted means of maintaining social order, legitimizes subversion of free will in general by way of the leadership examples set by the authority. That is, it becomes acceptable and even expected that social and business dealings <b>should</b> involve selfish motives which extend unto achieving personal goals by any means necessary, as long as said means are within the behavior code. Obviously there can be no <b>COMPLETE </b>code of behavior, any more than there could be an atlas of clouds, so, ill-informed and guided solely by fear of punishment, every strong person becomes a predator, and everyone else a victim.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; font-size: 20px\">Herein lies the basis for terror and dysfunction of sexuality among youth and adults. When every adult is expected or permitted to make decisions for others, no impropriety is acknowledged when consent for sex is subverted, provided statutory stipulations are satisfied, but impropriety it still may be!</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; font-size: 20px\">To make someone\'s mind up for them is always improper unless the matter is one of group safety or self defense. In sexual matters especially, objective, un-coerced consent is the only valid consent. But <b><i><span style=\"font-size: 1.5em;\">those in the habit of choosing for others will view any opportunity for sex involving potentially vulnerable people as fundamentally improper</span></i></b>. Such is only the case when respect for the autonomy, knowledge, and valid, legitimate consent of the vulnerable, is violated by unscrupulous, selfish subversion of will.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; font-size: 20px\"><center>end</center>\n</div>','2022-07-24 19:19:30',145,72,'whitehot robot','domination and respect','#psychology #morality #ethics',0,0,''),(600075,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; line-height: 1em;  font-size: 20px; color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify;\">Dear ma\'am,</div><di