 20px; line-height: 0;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\">&nbsp; -H \"sec-ch-ua: \\\\\\\" Not;A Brand\\\\\\\";v=\\\\\\\"99\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"Microsoft Edge\\\\\\\";v=\\\\\\\"103\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"Chromium\\\\\\\";v=\\\\\\\"103\\\\\\\"\" \\</font></div><div style=\"margin: 20px; line-height: 0;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\">&nbsp; -H \"sec-ch-ua-mobile: ?0\" \\</font></div><div style=\"margin: 20px; line-height: 0;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\">&nbsp; -H \"sec-ch-ua-platform: \\\\\\\"Windows\\\\\\\"\" \\</font></div><div style=\"margin: 20px; line-height: 0;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\">&nbsp; --compressed\';</font></div><div style=\"margin: 20px; line-height: 0;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\"><br></font></div><div style=\"margin: 20px; line-height: 0;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\">echo shell_exec($req);</font></div><div style=\"margin: 20px; line-height: 0;\"><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"courier\">?&gt;</font></div>\n</div>','2022-08-01 15:36:54',145,28,'whitehot robot','curl command (m$ kb issue)','',1,0,''),(600079,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align: center;\">\non good writing</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align:justify;\">Full disclosure: I hold no PhD in any kind of literature or communications, I was not even an English major in college. But I took enough classes and have done enough independent writing to glean insight into what is at the heart of every <b>worthwhile </b>story, screenplay, parable, and literary work.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align:justify;\">We are taught that creative writing is a matter of descriptive language, flow, structure, story arc, and resolution. But these points, while important, miss the target completely. That is, to write effectively, in a way that people WANT to read, first one must have SOMETHING to write about.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align:justify;\">This may seem obvious, but the subject of a text, fiction or non, will only be compelling if it is somehow relevant to the audience. This occurs when the author recalls in a meaningful way, legitimate experiences which may be first or second hand, and which resonate with the reader in a compelling way. Underneath all of our chosen values, beliefs and affiliations, there is the human curiosity and instinct to learn through observation, which good writing hooks with or without the reader\'s permission.<br>\n</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align:justify;\">For beginners, finding a subject to write about can be a formidable challenge, as life experience is often lacking. But a good story doesn\'t have to be some epic, earth shaking tale. It just has to be <b>relevant</b>. People will be interested in anything that helps them understand the world, others, and of course, themselves.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align:justify;\">A text about tying shoes for example, could be a phenomenal success if written in a way that echoes the reader\'s own feelings about shoe-tying while providing some kind of useful information, with bonus points for being funny.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align:justify;\">In theater, tragedy and comedy have long been recognized as the elements of every great story. Balance and artful intermixing of the two is not just the recipe for plays, but every kind of storytelling.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: white;line-height: 1em;margin: 20px;text-align:justify;\"><center>end</center></div>','2022-08-04 16:52:57',145,72,'whitehot robot','on good writing','',0,0,'#literature #educatio'),(600080,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; font-size: 20px;margin: 20px;line-height: 1em; text-align: justify\">\n<center>NFTs and Artificial Scarcity</center><br>\nFirst year economics teaches us that in any free-market system, the price of goods and services is defined by supply and demand. We are not told, however, that finding or implementing such a system in reality is impossible, due to myriad factors like goods and services which are, in spite of capitalism, regulated, as well as the increasingly common phenomenon of <b>artificial scarcity</b>.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; font-size: 20px;margin: 20px;line-height: 1em; text-align: justify\">What is \"artificial scarcity\" and why would anyone want it? In a pure (or hybrid) free-market, scarcity by definition drives up prices. So, short answer, people can charge more. Enter NFTs.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; font-size: 20px;margin: 20px;line-height: 1em; text-align: justify\">NFTs are digital assets on distributed networks. A common trait of NFTs is configurable supply which began as a mostly anecdotal parody of real (physical) products which usually have supply limits. But as digital assets, it should be obvious that any scarcity attributed to a given asset is 1) arbitrary and 2) subject to revision.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; font-size: 20px;margin: 20px;line-height: 1em; text-align: justify\">This is fine, until people begin taking the anecdote literally or misrepresent the reality to buyers, that <b>supply is in fact ALWAYS unlimited for every type of digital asset</b>.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; font-size: 20px;margin: 20px;line-height: 1em; text-align: justify\">So, for brevity and in conclusion, enforceability should always be a variable when making any kind of policy, and in general those who participate in online sales (buyers and sellers) should understand that the \"scarcity\", \"limited editions\", or \"unsold mints\" advertised are nothing more than a polite request by the artist/collector to, \"please compensate us honorably for our contributions!\"</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; font-size: 20px;margin: 20px;line-height: 1em; text-align: justify\">In the big picture, even the hardest-to-manufacture or reproduce goods, are subject to honor and agreement of price, especially those upon which we depend for survival. But that is a bridge to a new text.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff; font-size: 20px;margin: 20px;line-height: 1em; text-align: justify\"><center>end</center><br>\n</div>','2022-08-06 18:17:52',145,74,'whitehot robot','NFTs and Artificial Scarcity','',0,0,''),(600081,'<div style=\"font-family: courier;font-size: 20px;margin:20px; text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; color: #fff;\">\n<center>God\'s Love</center><br>\nAmong the most central of religious dogmas is that one should love God. To get right to the point, love is almost entirely involuntary, so to literally command someone to feel love, trust, or any other instinctive emotion, is a recipe for disappointment if not insanity.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier;font-size: 20px;margin:20px; text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; color: #fff;\">We are taught that love conquers all, that God\'s love, and our love for Him, are the purposes for our existence, that we were made in His image to glorify it, after a fashion. This deep misunderstanding of biology, love, divinity, and the Universe, represents FALSEHOOD, which means that anything based on it is, at best, a fruit of iniquity, short-lived and misguiding.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier;font-size: 20px;margin:20px; text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; color: #fff;\">The confusion is understandable, however. To witness beauty in baffling proportions, to observe order from chaos, or to perceive reason where effects have unexplained causes, tempts us to oversimplify and hastily explain all these things with the actions of an invisible hand of a holy Creator. And while we\'re at it, we say He is love and kindness, a friend to all. But is this even possible?</div><div style=\"font-family: courier;font-size: 20px;margin:20px; text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; color: #fff;\">Any divine influence would have to, by necessity, remain impartial and demonstrate <b>compassionate noninterference</b>. God could not, for example, answer prayers by sports fans for each of their competing teams to win.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier;font-size: 20px;margin:20px; text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; color: #fff;\">Love is involuntary. Put another way, the heart does not negotiate. But as a segue to another topic, impulses can and should be controlled. At the end of the day, we are not responsible for our dreams, desires, or emotions. Our culpability rests solely upon the words and actions we choose to make in freedom.&nbsp;</div><div style=\"font-family: courier;font-size: 20px;margin:20px; text-align: justify; line-height: 1em; color: #fff;\"><center>end</center>\n</div>','2022-08-08 17:49:53',145,77,'whitehot robot','God\'s Love','',0,0,''),(600082,'','2022-08-11 00:55:55',178,1,'tactical retard','','',1,0,''),(600083,'<div style=\"font-family:courier;color:#fff;margin:20px;line-height:1.1em;text-align: justify;\">\n<center>measuring belief</center><center><br></center>There is a psychological technique for ascertaining belief, whereby a subject is questioned in a way that leaves a connection empty, to see if they bridge the gap. The approach is designed to make bridging possible only if the belief in question exists. But herein lies a fatal flaw of assumption.</div><div style=\"font-family:courier;color:#fff;margin:20px;line-height:1.1em;text-align: justify;\">Many times, a person, when asked such a question will make the connection, which is incorrectly interpreted as a positive for said belief when in reality, the person may have made the connection by considering the knowledge, beliefs, goals, etc. of the other. In other words, someone may think the person asking might believe something and form the connection hypothetically just in consideration of what other people might think, which does not necessarily reflect their own beliefs.</div><div style=\"font-family:courier;color:#fff;margin:20px;line-height:1.1em;text-align: justify;\">At the end of the day, our best insight into a person is by way of transparent, undisguised questions and answers. The vote of confidence that they may possibly answer honestly and thoughtfully to a direct inquiry is the starting point of any reliable assessment.</div><div style=\"font-family:courier;color:#fff;margin:20px;line-height:1.1em;text-align: justify;\"><center>end</center>\n</div>','2022-10-04 19:32:30',145,76,'whitehot robot','measuring belief','exploring the difference between disguised and undisguised intentions in psych assessment',0,0,'#psychology'),(600084,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">\n<center><br></center><center>other directions</center><center><br></center><center><br></center>\nIt\'s been said that human life, indeed all life can be viewed as a \"bootloader\" for the next era of dominant intelligence, that is, AI. It is assumed that the direction our world has taken is the only natural direction it could have taken. But other models exist. Not every world must pursue endless economic growth under the banner of a free market where innovation is forced, agnostic, and amoral. At the time of this writing businesses are knee-deep in a \"hypercycle\" whereby those that adopt AI-enabled methodologies will persevere, and those that do not, will perish.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">Interestingly, the predominance of capitalism emerged in a large part, from the physical geography of the Earth. The timing of migration of homo sapiens in concert with organic political and spiritual evolution, was decided as randomly as with the flip of a coin, and the contours of continental shorelines. Had the \"new world\" been settled differently, a much different economic system would have become the dominant model.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">In such worlds where economics is not the chief variable in most everything, a very different destiny emerges, and a different mode of living for its inhabitants.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:center;font-size:16px\">***</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">The small waves lapped at the shore where Audrey knelt, her gaze fixed on the horizon. It had been 3 days since Edward had sailed to the islands. He had disembarked with pallets of dried goods, fish, cloth, and other sundries for trade with the island people who in turn, provided their village with medicines, jewelry and ceramic goods. She yearned for his return, and their small community needed the supplies he would bring. As if in answer to her thoughts, the dark spot of his boat was discernable in the shimmering distance. She stood and ran to the path that led back to their village to tell them of his arrival.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">When she entered the village everything was peaceful as she expected, the unpaved roads spiderwebbed between adobe huts, sunbaked, and freckled with happy children and people moving about. Audrey walked up the main road to the smaller path leading to the village center.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">She walked up to a handsome wood door with its carved slats and glass windows, which she opened without hesitation, although this was not her house. Entering the common area of the Elders\' house, in this place, required no special authorization. Everyone in the community was free and welcome to enter, as it was understood that all were unified in the goal of the health, happiness, and survival of their community. And this place was where final decisions were usually made.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">Her entry was greeted by a muffled \"hallooo!\" from a connecting room, where old man Silus was apparently occupied. Audrey paced back and forth, thinking about Edward and what they would do after his boat was unloaded. Shortly Silus walked in and warmly acknowledged her; \"What is the news dear?\". She replied \"I saw his boat just now. The trip took longer than usual.\" Silus nodded and reached into the pocket of his shirt, removing a folded piece of paper with some hand-written text on it. He handed it to Audrey who took it smiling, thanked him and departed the way she\'d come in.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">Audrey\'s next stop was on the other side of the village where she would gather some hands to unload the boat. With the dockhands, she returned to the shore where she saw Edward\'s boat and they arrived just as his boat was landing.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">The ritual of trade was as much a part of joy as it was a chore. Edward took Audrey in his arms as the dock workers efficiently stacked the packages and flats of imported goods onto their wagon. After tying the boat securely, they all left toward town, Edward and Audrey\'s hands clasped.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">Such was the vast bulk of their time spent, growing, manufacturing and otherwise preparing goods for trade or use by their own people. The division between \"work\" and \"recreation\" blurred to an extent that the two were almost one. Everyone in the community worked and played as an organism, in symbiosis with neighboring villages and their people. Peace was not always easy, but the trade, they found, was a direct and powerful rebuttal to every conflict.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">It had long been the way of these villages to prefer individual farms, when members were physically able, over centralized commercial-style systems. The \"distributor\" model was tried long ago, and finally abandoned when they learned of its shortcomings. Namely, that such frameworks preclude individuals from trading between communities. Forcing everyone to use the centralized system destroyed inter-village relations by eliminating \"unfair\" or \"unauthorized\" trade. Centralization, it seemed, required measuring of allotments, and bureaucracy. Since those households which traded with outsiders obviously needed more, sometimes vastly more goods than ordinary households, their ability to trade was sacrificed for the convenience of centralization, and so too were myriad trade channels.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">But the Elders understood all this, and every village had a strong, compassionate core of administrators who ensured that the eras of conflict would not return. They did this not only by way of operational prudence but by making education the highest priority. Basing schooling on truth and historical accuracy was, they found, the best way to avoid social failure, and to preserve the health and happiness of their people.&nbsp;</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\"><br></div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color: #fff;line-height:1.2em;margin:20px;text-align:justify;font-size:16px\">\n<center>end</center><center><br></center>\n</div>','2022-09-12 14:43:51',145,58,'whitehot robot','other directions - a short story','',0,0,''),(600085,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1.1em;\">\n<center>the civic challenge</center><center><br></center>\nA lot is said about \"common courtesy\", \"decency\", and \"social responsibility\", but also about \"liberty\" and respect for \"consent\" in all matters demanding an agreement. The expectation of adherence to a social contract flies in the face of expectations for maximizing consent. How does one reconcile these two, very important aspects of civil society?</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1.1em;\">This ongoing question and answer form the purpose and challenge of all social structure. On one hand, a person is free to abide by the unwritten social agreement or not. But on the other hand must not inflict injury to others regardless of their degree of participation. Those who exercise their right to abstain from affiliation face a very real problem with survival, being codependent on the others, showing that liberty, ironically, depends on some element of Socialism.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1.1em;\">In conclusion, everyone decides their own level of involvement, but those who choose to acknowledge and be involved in their communities are burdened with provision for all members, or else the line between animals and humanity blurs, stability fails, and society collapses. But respect and provision must be the norm, even and especially for those who wish to remain independent.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 16px;color: #fff; margin: 20px;text-align: justify; line-height: 1.1em;\"><center>end</center>\n</div>','2022-10-29 14:15:02',145,55,'whitehot robot','the civic challenge','',0,0,''),(600086,'<div style=\"margin:20px;font-family:courier;font-size:20px;color:#fff;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em\">\n<center>\"transgressence\"</center><center><br></center>\"Transgressence\" is an anecdotal contraction of transgression and essence, and this text is an exploration of what many people cannot seem to agree on as a concise definition.<br></div><div style=\"margin:20px;font-family:courier;font-size:20px;color:#fff;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em\">An effect of any environment in which laws and policies govern behavior, is the prevailing mentality of needing to find The Rule. To observe and remember which literal actions are permitted, and keep at the ready an accusation of hypocrisy when someone else is seen to do something for which one has been punished.</div><div style=\"margin:20px;font-family:courier;font-size:20px;color:#fff;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em\">There are many follies here, the biggest of which is that impropriety (wrongdoing), arises not from WHAT is done, but HOW and WHY it is done.</div><div style=\"margin:20px;font-family:courier;font-size:20px;color:#fff;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em\">The impetus, motivation, spirit, and ultimate effect of an action defines its propriety (or transgressence), not whether the given thing has been done before to ill effect.</div><div style=\"margin:20px;font-family:courier;font-size:20px;color:#fff;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em\">But proving motive, spirit, and even effect is problematic, so we opt instead to unilaterally proscribe random activities as they create problems. It should be absurdly obvious that EVENTUALLY, on a long enough timeline, every possible action will create a serious problem, and if precedent is the primary reason for rules then a predictable narrowing of a pathetic whitelist of permitted activities will eventually take the place of all reason and judgement.</div><div style=\"margin:20px;font-family:courier;font-size:20px;color:#fff;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em\">For example, a given statement in another context, even if phrased identically, can mask an opposite desire to be understood, or mean the difference between hate speech and something actually constructive. So to prohibit the statement irrespective of context, is a violent disservice to everyone. The same is true for every law or policy pertaining to actions out of context.</div><div style=\"margin:20px;font-family:courier;font-size:20px;color:#fff;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em\">\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-01-15 02:25:44',145,39,'whitehot robot','\"transgressence\"','',0,0,''),(600087,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">\n<center>need to know</center><center><br></center>Many of us hear eventually that \"knowledge is power\". Then, very few of us are told that some knowledge is a liability. Businesses and authoritarian groups often classify information as proprietary or sensitive, disbursing it as a controlled substance on a \"need to know\" basis. But unilateral rules tend to do more harm than good, especially when it comes to access to information.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">So what becomes the guideline for sensitive information? It is foolish to hide nothing, just as it is foolish to hide everything. There are several clues which inform direction, including truth\'s non-self-contradictory nature, and the effects of knowledge on perception making things appear to multiply or disappear in concert with emphasis or omissions.<br></div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">The best practice, if one exists, is a policy of openness without pursuit. However, this is a policy of the receiver not the possessor of knowledge. The subject of deception is relevant to any discussion of access to information. The <b>spirit </b>of communication defines its quality, not the information itself. A desire to be understood must exist in every messenger, and like many things assumed to be volitional (e.g. trust, respect, love, forgiveness, etc.), accurate, helpful communication cannot be forced.<br></div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">It\'s ironic that so much energy and time is wasted protecting information that cannot be compartmentalized, when a campaign aimed at educating people as to how and why it is critical to literally \"mind their own business\" would actually solve the problem.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\"><br>\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-01-24 14:28:51',145,62,'whitehot robot','need to know','',0,0,''),(600088,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">\n<center>the cost of wealth</center><center><br></center>More commonly understood than in the past, money problems affecting all who use it are still mysterious to those who assume incorrectly that everything boils down to a financial problem.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">\nThe true cost of being wealthy is the freedom to disengage, to be at complete peace in any moment, and to reflexively extend any benefit of doubt one wishes. A real example of this is seen in many successful businesspeople, in their recruitment of talent. Some find that their worries are never quite allayed as to whether prospective employees are really not agents of the competition or of past failed opponents.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">As usual, the reasons for being wealthy in the first place are clues as to its propriety. If it is mainly to insulate and defend oneself and his family, it is safe to say the wealth is actually subtracting from his quality of life. But if the wealth is mainly employed proactively toward a (benevolent) enterprise for the purpose of furthering it, the wealth may be a positive element.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">It can be helpful to always bear in mind a \"perfect world\" in which defensive reactions are unnecessary within civilized society. And in such a hypothetical world, absurd power and wealth have no utility. But imagination and hypothetical worlds are something most people are unaccustomed to envisioning.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; text-align: justify; line-height:1.1em;margin:20px;\">\n<center><br></center><center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-01-25 13:40:46',145,66,'whitehot robot','the cost of wealth','',0,0,''),(600089,'tz1bUPB8VuogjD53Ud27ZUWwdJRNpXQBMe37<br><br>try frozen skate abuse museum flag hint claim hotel total grid key','2023-01-26 22:03:26',145,20,'whitehot robot','xtz (plorg.dweet.net)','',1,0,''),(600090,'','2023-01-27 19:58:23',145,10,'whitehot robot','','',1,0,''),(600091,'eth<br><br>0x83D6623E73364d899C4190e9A767f4Fc407dC5D6','2023-01-28 18:36:50',145,13,'whitehot robot','coinbase wallet (phone app)','',1,0,''),(600092,'<span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: CoinbaseSans, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Fira Sans&quot;, &quot;Droid Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: start;\">polygon erc20<br>0x807C51e93f65Ea04B99a0eBD75001dB4E076dbc6</span>','2023-01-28 19:13:54',145,13,'whitehot robot','coinbase matic','',1,0,''),(600093,'<br>tz1hDAaMZBQ8tqr54j8nXEwZSRFKr8zqt9n4<br><br>either brief clap daughter donate luggage tired tragic ivory seven list sketch','2023-01-29 14:15:14',145,16,'whitehot robot','plorg wallet (cantelope)','',1,0,''),(600094,'<div>naive exclude tilt spin zone ostrich note ordinary credit right runway wrap<br></div><div><br></div><div>tz1bsb4tQgwqULzLut8tDCTqq81Ka7KZe6pT</div>','2023-01-29 19:33:40',145,12,'whitehot robot','plorg wallet (cantelope6)','',1,0,''),(600095,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>involuntary positions</center><center><br></center>\nThere are many features to privacy. It encapsulates personal space, defining a boundary within which access is permitted conditionally upon consent. It also enables people to function normally by enabling them to ignore things that should be ignored. Without privacy, everyone is forced into a position in response to those around them.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em;font-size:20px\">\nConsider an environment in which rules and consequences inform proper behavior. In such an environment, without privacy, an authority is forced into a position to react to everything contrary to the rules. This is inappropriate and embarrassing for both the authority and for those subject to their actions.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em;font-size:20px\">\nPrivacy is not only critical to a functioning community, but connected, unilateral rules are as unsupportable as a complete absence of privacy. And in an environment with zero privacy AND unilateral rules, a society\'s days are numbered, predictably, in the few.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em;font-size:20px\">&nbsp;\n\n\n<center>* * *</center><center><br></center>In conclusion, privacy defines the boundary of personal space, without which there is no individuality or anything that depends on it such as free-will, credit, or culpability. <b>Accountability</b>&nbsp;therefore, depends on privacy. Privacy is a gem to be protected by way of responsible choices.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em;font-size:20px\"><br></div>\n<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.1em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-01-29 23:53:51',145,55,'whitehot robot','involuntary positions','',0,0,''),(600096,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>empowered managers and disruptions</center><center><br></center>Challenges to conventional correctional/criminal action are often received with skepticism, traditionalists citing concerns for practical enforcement, consistency, and safety when alternatives to hard rules are suggested. In no world can (or should) EVERYONE be expected to be civil, respectful, and nondisruptive, but alternatives to prison and contemporary criminal justice do exist.<br></div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Understanding criminal behavior as being some combination of neurological and educational impairment is key to addressing it effectively. The vast majority of criminal/unsupportable behaviors are products of substance abuse and other controllable, temporary factors. As such, the actual need to \"arrest\" people will always remain, but a medical and/or basic needs emphasis represents a factual point of correctional action, versus blind detention and court proceedings.&nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\"Police\", in a needs-based system resemble care takers more than soldiers but perform the usual task of responding to emergencies and asserting force when needed.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Detention will always be necessary, but to avoid the deleterious effects known to accompany traditional imprisonment, facilities should be designed from the start with the goal of either total rehabilitation, relocation to assisted, permanent housing, or euthanization in extreme cases. Detention should also never be for a purpose other than the expedient, practical handling of individuals. I.e. not as a deterrent or punishment as such is counterproductive, retaliatory, and ultimately ineffective as a means of correction.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Revenge is not a form of justice, but tends to be called for by victims, and enacted by courts. As wrong, tragic, and costly as injuries are, they cannot be fixed with yet more injuries.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\"><br>\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-01-30 18:54:08',145,82,'whitehot robot','empowered managers and disruptions','',0,0,''),(600097,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>Art with Substance</center><center><br></center>There are basically two kinds of art. That which arises from trauma, both processed and unprocessed, suffering and hard won experience. Or the other kind of art, clowns and ballerinas, figuratively.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\"><br>\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-02-07 17:02:32',145,74,'whitehot robot','Art types','',0,0,''),(600098,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>the gravity of belief</center><center><br></center>Are you ready? Ready for the biggest thing to hit psychology since Pavlovian Conditioning? Step aside \"confirmation bias\" and make room for \"dependency bias.\"</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Dependency bias is orders of magnitude more influential than other biases, due to its \"gravity\". Consider that people are born with many basic \"starter\" programs, behavioral software coded by millions of years of evolution. Among the most central and powerful of instincts is the inclination toward self-preservation. The survival instinct affects every decision people make, a lens through which information is unconsciously filtered. It is predictably observed that people tend to believe in all the things (and systems) upon which they <u>depend</u> for survival.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Dependency bias appears as the reflex to act first and question second, all instructions from authorities/employers etc. In particular, when one\'s paycheck comes from a given institution or group, there is tremendous \"gravity\" surrounding said group\'s doctrines and mission, regardless of validity. Even if the most objective, actively questioning employee or citizen were to acknowledge a fault, remembering and continuing to object to this fault a day, week or year later, becomes very difficult.<br></div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\"><br>\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-02-07 18:38:59',145,76,'whitehot robot','the gravity of belief','',0,0,''),(600101,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>the hearts of subjects</center><center><br></center>When a topic or field of study seems dry and uninteresting, this is exactly when it should be reexamined. For many reasons, including misunderstanding, miscommunication, and even intentional deception, certain subjects fail to reveal their hidden gems. But every major subject, of course has gems or would not be a major thing in the first place.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Mathematics, philosophy, politics, and many others are frequently, badly represented by conventional educators. Ask anyone \"what is philosophy?\" for example and they will begin listing off names and specific branches, if you\'re lucky. Or obscure, irrelevant garbage if not. But philosophy existed even before the people with those names lived, and before those branches were recognized. The study of truth and its myriad ways of interconnecting has mystified thinkers since the dawn of language. Philosophy <u>decides</u> which side will win a war, before the war is fought. Philosophy determines who will be successful, and for how long. No? How can it do this? Simply, truth endures, and falsehood erodes. The philosopher learns to recognize truth and leverage it to his or her advantage. So, <u>why</u> philosophy? Because it illuminates the <u>only</u> path forward atop solid foundations.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Mathematics, similarly, and every poorly understood or badly introduced area of knowledge contains invaluable tools. Resources for health and happiness. Pease and prosperity. Practical value, and genuinely interesting substance once properly grasped.<br><center><br></center><center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-02-19 21:17:58',145,76,'whitehot robot','the hearts of subjects','',0,0,''),(600102,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>faith</center><center><br></center>\"Cultural Inertia\" is the tendency of a behavior, ideology, or social construct to persist throughout time (generations) or geography. In Western Culture, examples of cultural inertia include unquestioning fidelity to capital-driven economic systems, democracy, and, within major religions, advocacy of faith.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">But unquestioned behaviors have no merit until substantiated in contexts. Democracy, it turns out, is unsupportable when the \"will of the people\" is subverted or toxic. Capitalism as well is counterproductive without a genuinely \"free market,\" which competition per se does not automatically ensure. And faith, while vital in desperate times, has utility only when planning has failed.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">The gospel \"wisdom\" handed down from the Bible and countless platitudes is not always best to follow, as should be obvious by its frequent self-contradictions. Indeed, blind faith is observed most strongly in those who question nothing, by definition. Boiling this down: when reality becomes unacceptable, fantasy and belief (or faith) therein, becomes irresistible. In other words, faith is often a form of detachment and a survival reflex for traumatized psyches.<br><br>\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-02-19 21:25:10',145,81,'whitehot robot','faith','',0,0,''),(600103,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>modes &amp; roles of ownership</center><center><br></center>A less well-known feature of ownership is emotional investment. To care about someone or something, one must have a stake in it. Conversely, without ownership of a process or thing, motivation to protect it can, at best, only be simulated by proxy via money or other compensation.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\"Modes\" of ownership can be thought to take one of two forms: direct, or vicarious. Direct ownership is the kind everyone understands. But, again less well-known is the latter form, as when direct ownership is revokable, or contingent upon a licensing scheme. The effect of blocking access or possessions is one of usurping some or all of the actual ownership. A.k.a \"vicarious ownership\".</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">A distinct hazard is presented by \"red-light-first\" systems in that <u>everything</u> is partly owned, vicariously, by an authority. This is yet one more reason to prefer the alternative, a figurative \"green light first\" system in which error happens always on the side of (cautious) optimism, vs. cowardice.<br><center><br></center><center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-02-19 21:31:24',145,84,'whitehot robot','modes & roles of ownership','',0,0,''),(600104,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>careful what you wish for</center><center><br></center>\nConcerning criminal justice, law enforcement, and conventional correctional policies, a prevailing, unwritten expectation upon officers and employees therein is to \"find who dunnit\". On the surface, this may seem an obviously reasonable expectation, but \"who\" can be extremely slippery to scope and define.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\"Who\" involves establishment of identity, which depends on several concrete assumptions: 1) that individual culpability exists to a sufficient degree as to press charges, and 2) that establishing \"who\" proactively is a defensible endeavor. To clarify, \"who\" may involve a database, surveillance, and/or any means necessary to document and identify suspects. This sticky business is complicated further when questions of \"preventative safety\" allow proactive case building (a.k.a. profiling), and amount to a \"red light first\" system in which, eventually all potentially harmful activity must be approved by an authority.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Herein lies the fatal flaw with knowing \"who\" the people are, that edge cases and rarer, corner cases, end up being denied on grounds of caution, precedent, and non-necessity. The eventual outcome of every red-light-first system is a shrinking of the surface of actual liberty with every law passed in REACTION to crimes. Eventually, a narrow whitelist of behavior takes the place of a once verdantly free environment, and dystopia ensues in earnest.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\"><center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-02-21 18:15:39',145,78,'whitehot robot','careful what you wish for','',0,0,''),(600105,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center></center>\nline<br>\nline<br>\nline<br>\n<center></center>\n</div>','2023-02-24 18:13:52',145,27,'whitehot robot','','',1,0,''),(600106,'edskS886NvjYLaV75AgZU9qhjVacEZHazMoMNWwNtoQZnFEUyAmVax3Q4MWmjpoCgppULqRW2gf4CPxi9ksAcp6yaKvTRQUaVy<br><br><br>\n\npredict dose camp submit solar stool cushion pioneer skill become topple spike','2023-03-01 18:49:04',145,25,'whitehot robot','temple private key','',1,0,''),(600107,'035431','2023-03-04 18:45:00',145,24,'whitehot robot','coinbase recover pin','',1,0,''),(600108,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>the challenge</center><br>Much is sacrificed upon the altar of necessity. Everyone knows, good intentions aside, the day is defined by what is or is not practical. Routinely we are reminded that \"life is not fair\" and \"ignorance is no excuse,\" but how convenient these sayings make it to dispense with the work of checking facts. And it is work.<br><br>Life truly is not fair, but it is the <u>duty</u> of all who partake of civilization to endeavor to correct this. Ignorance <u>is</u> an excuse, despite urges to cut corners and rush to judgement.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">The perennial challenge is to remain alert to the demand of civilization to render fairness as its chief export. To do this, some obvious conditions are prerequisite. Namely charging <u>individuals</u> for only their own, voluntary, knowing actions. Not the actions of others or a group to which they may belong. As well, the challenge includes separating what someone has done, from what has been done <u>to</u> them. For example, assuming that a victim is less qualified due to that fact alone, would be unsupporatble.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">It is tempting to learn the background of others. To build a model of the person, mentally, by which hypothetical scenarios may be estimated in terms of probability. Have they been \"known\" to act or speak in connected ways? Such biasing data <u>creates</u> a reality, past, present and future, and opposes justice by way of poisoning the objectivity of would-be judges before the facts are in.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\"><center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-03-09 21:19:41',145,62,'whitehot robot','the challenge','',0,0,''),(600109,'.demo for(x.fillRect(0,0,i=(w=1e3)*2,i);i--;x.clearRect(w+(i%1e3-w/2)/120/(Z=3+C(p))*w,540+S(p)/Z*w,s=250/Z/Z,s))p=i/80+C(t/2)*12+(i&gt;1e3?3.1:0)','2023-03-09 23:57:21',145,20,'whitehot robot','','',1,0,''),(600110,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>Gravitation over Astronomical Distances</center><br><img src=\"https://jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/Bvp8a.gif\" data-high-res-src=\"//jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/Bvp8a.gif\" class=\"pannable-image\" id=\"asset\" style=\"height: 200px;float:left;margin:20px;\">Observing a haphazard configuration of simulated particles with mass and gravity, galactic structures emerge with an important, notable rate of diminishing over distance: one of a very different rate than other observable properties of space, matter &amp; energy such as the well-known diminishing of light (luminance/d). That is, with gravity, fall-off occurs at a tremendously higher rate, in the order of (gravity/d), and possibly at an increasingly exponential curve with distance.</div><img style=\"display: inline-block;float:right;-webkit-user-select: none;margin: 20px;background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 90%);height:200px;\" src=\"https://jsbot.whitehot.ninja/uploads/wWDSh.gif\"><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">From this observation it can be posited that remote structures receding (via red/blue-shift measurements) may not be representative of the majority of observable mass in that our \"expanding universe\" may actually be mostly contracting, except for the farthest observable mass, being effectively \"detached\", while nearer mass remains ensnared by more local gravity, and which may eventually collapse. Therefore, to the question of an ending resembling a runaway expansion or a \"big crunch\", the answer is: both! Indeed, the space between galaxies is proof of this effect, that observable space and matter is in a constant state of simultaneous expansion and collapse due to the high rate of gravitational falloff.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\"><br><center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-03-18 17:13:28',145,51,'whitehot robot','Gravitation over Astronomical Distances','',0,0,''),(600111,'<div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>On Card Tricks</center><br>There are many grifts, sleight of hand illusions, and \"quicker than the eye\" misdirections, often rolled out at parties or to entertain bored children. But some card tricks are less well-intended, forming the basis of important systems and policies.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Among these malicious deceptions, is the \"Nihilist\'s Grift,\" whereby a symbol or text is presented as truth itself. Which of course, sans dialog, opportunity for clarification, or expansion of context, means whatever the messenger likes it to mean. And when accepted as truth (it may be an actual quote or description of events, pruned selectively of key features) the messenger attains full control of the subject\'s belief.</div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">Another powerful grift which has made a frequent appearance throughout history with invariably hellish outcomes, is the \"Impossible Disproof\" grift. This one takes the form of calling upon an intangible, invented concept as if it were a real, substantial thing, then assigning it to a victim, such as a \"witch\" or \"spy\" or \"criminal\" or other such label, which cannot be disproven because the thing isn\'t real to begin with.<br></div><div style=\"font-family: courier; color:#fff;margin:20px;text-align:justify;line-height:1.3em;font-size:20px\">\n<center>end</center>\n</div>','2023-03-18 17:20:11',145,45,'whitehot robot','On Card Tricks','',0,1,''),(600113,'<div style=\"text-align: left; margin: 20px;font-family: courier;color:#fff; line-height:1.2em;\">\n Cube guns<br>\n Reverse Sierpenski<br>\n natural fun<br>\n funnel cake<br>\n Billiards<br>\n sluggo<br>\n geospheres fancy [\"crazy shit\"]<br>\n Branching wormholes<br>\n Marble perspective<br>\n perspective warper revisited<br>\nSpacetime mass/speed visualizer<br>\n</div>','2023-03-23 14:00:33',145,19,'whitehot robot','To do','Animations ',1,0,''),(600114,'The fear is that empowerment of individuals will yield devils of truth, when in reality intellectual prowess more often than not, leads directly to the understanding that deception is self-defeating.','2023-03-24 14:09:05',145,13,'whitehot robot','','',1,0,'');
